title: hot punch
directions: You will need a 30 cup percolator.

title: crawfish macltshoe
directions: Cut and clean corn; add everything together except crawfish tails.
Cook on medium heat, adding water when needed for about 45 minutes.
Now add crawfish and cook for 20 minutes.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add oil, eggs, apple and nuts.
Mix together by hand until moist.
Pour into greased and
floured 11 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream or whipping cream or serves great as morning coffee cake.

title: chocolate peanut butter banana whirlwinds
directions: Cut the banana into 1-inch pieces.
Wrap in foil and freeze for 5 minutes.
Unwrap banana pieces.
In a blender container, combine banana, milk, chocolate ice cream and peanut butter. Cover and blend until smooth.
Makes 3 (6 ounce) servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a casserole dish 45 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Grate and soak zucchini in salt water for 2 or more hours. Then mix eggs, bread crumbs, milk, flour, cheese and salt and pepper.
Squeeze zucchini and fold into batter mixture.
Fry in hot oil, spreading batter thinly.
Salt like French fries.

title: favorite chili
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper in heavy saucepan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, stirring until ground beef is crumbly; drain.
Combine tomato sauce, water, chili seasoning mix, chili powder, garlic powder, cumin, oregano and marjoram in bowl; mix well.
Add to ground beef.
Add tomatoes and beans; mix well.
Simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or to desired consistency, stirring frequently.
May add additional water if chili becomes too dry.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: 24 hour lettuce salad
directions: Shred lettuce in large glass bowl.
Sprinkle next 3 ingredients over top in layers.
Break peas apart and sprinkle over while frozen.
Spread mayonnaise like frosting.
Sprinkle sugar and enough cheese to cover top.
Cover and put in refrigerator for 24 hours or overnight.
Before serving, sprinkle top with eggs and Bac*Os and toss.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in baking pan (greased).
Pour all other ingredients over chicken.
Bake at 375° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Keep spooning liquid over chicken as it bakes.

title: oven-baked chicken and gravy
directions: Salt and pepper fryer.
Dip
cut-up
fryer in vegetable oil, then roll in flour.
Place in deep baking dish (greased). Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at
Remove
from
oven and turn each piece.
Bake another 10 minutes.
Pour 3 cups (2 milk and 1 water) or more
over
chicken;
completely cover.
Add additional salt and pepper.
Bake
minutes
more or until bubbling.

title: easy barbecue chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken pieces.
In a skillet, add chicken and cook over medium heat.
Brown and simmer on all sides.
Cook until chicken is tender (about 1 hour), turning skin-side down for the last half hour.
Remove chicken, skim off excess fat.
Serve sauce over chicken.
Delicious and easy. Enjoy.

title: martha's fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in a heavy 2 1/2-quart saucepan.
Bring to full rolling boil.
Stir constantly.
Continue boiling for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Continue stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool at room temperature and cut into squares.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and spices in bowl.
Add oats and raisins.
Mix well.
Beat eggs in small bowl.
Stir in oil, milk and vanilla. Add to dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls, 1/2-inch apart, onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: banana, nut, raisin and chocolate chip bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter or spray a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Puree bananas in a food processor.
Add sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla.
Process until blended with a mixer.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and nutmeg.
Process until combined.
Add walnuts, raisins and chocolate chips.
Stir well.
Pour batter into pan and smooth the top.
Bake until a toothpick inserted comes out clean, 60 to 70 minutes.
Let cool in pan on a wire rack, 10 minutes. Remove bread from pan and cool completely.

title: easy hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine cocoa and sugar in small saucepan; stir in milk. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla, stirring until butter melts.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Yields 1 1/3 cups.

title: saucepan peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the corn syrup and sugar in a medium saucepan.
Bring the mixture to a full boil.
Remove from the heat and stir in the peanut butter and corn flakes.
Mix well.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls onto a buttered baking sheet or wax paper.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: rolls
directions: Place Crisco, salt, sugar, yeast, egg and water in large bowl. Add flour all at once.
Work with hands until dough is kind of waxy.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or until ready.
Take out of refrigerator and knead down.
Make into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Brush tops with butter and serve hot.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour in a Bundt pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
While cake is still warm, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: fruit freeze
directions: Pour lemon juice over bananas.
Add sugar and orange juice. Add all other fruits; mash together.
Add water and stir.
Place in container and freeze.
Stir 2 or 3 times during freezing process.
Remove from freezer about 1/2 hour before eating.

title: confetti chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed until blended.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; beat into first mixture at low speed until blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop 2 level measuring tablespoonfuls of dough into mound for each cookie.
Place 3 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes.
(Cookies will appear moist.)
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet, then remove.
Do not overbake.
The cookies will finish cooking during 2 minute cooling time.

title: fat-free taco shells
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray corn tortillas on both sides with nonstick cooking spray.
Drape over oven racks to form the shells. Bake until crisp.
Fill with your favorite fillings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mash the potatoes. Add butter and sugar. Blend. Stir in milk, eggs, nutmeg, vanilla, then beat with mixer for about 5 minutes. Pour into 2 pastry shells.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Yields 2 pies.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, thoroughly mix 1/2 cup of the soup, the beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion and Worcestershire sauce in a 12 x 8-inch baking pan.
Firmly shape meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done; remove meat loaf to platter.
Keep warm.
Serve gravy with meat loaf.

title: look like dirt cake
directions: In small bowl, mix with beater the margarine, cream cheese and 10x sugar.
In another bowl, combine milk and pudding; beat until creamy and thick.
Add cream cheese mixture; continue beating until well mixed.
Now fold in Cool Whip.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Roll graham crackers into crumbs; pour over butter and press in with a spoon.
Sprinkle the chocolate chips, nuts and coconut in layers over this.
Pour milk evenly over all and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: baked squash
directions: Peel slices of squash.
Place in 8 x 10-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with salt and cinnamon.
Spread approximately 1 teaspoon of brown sugar on each slice of squash.
Put dots of margarine on top of brown sugar.
Pour enough water into pan to keep squash from sticking and burning to the pan.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 375°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Dissolve soda in raisin water.
Add sifted flour, spices and rolled oats.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Chill before serving.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine sugar and flour, then stir in juice.
Add cheese and pineapple and mix well.
Spoon mixture into a 1-quart flat oiled dish.
Combine butter and cracker crumbs; sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crumbs are lightly browned.
This is an easy to double or triple recipe.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender.
Makes 1 quart.
Delicious on sandwiches too!

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Pour dressing over combined vegetables.
Cover and marinate. Arrange vegetables on skewers.
Broil 5 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Brush with remaining marinade.

title: cucumber sandwich
directions: Mix cream cheese with milk.
Add salt, basil, oregano and onion.
Mix well.
Spread on thin sliced cocktail rye.
Place a slice of cucumber on top.
Sprinkle with dill weed.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in milk, then dry mixture.
Pour butter over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: pickled celery
directions: Pack each jar with
celery,
garlic seed and dill seed. Add hot pepper.
Bring	vinegar,
water
and salt to a rolling boil. Pour over celery and seasonings.
Seal.

title: zucchini-apple pie
directions: Toss together zucchini, lemon juice and salt.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Add the zucchini and mix well.
Mixture will be runny.
Place the filling in a 9-inch crust and dot with butter.
Add top crust and bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in tablespoon of butter until soft.
After soft, stir in flour and add water.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thick.
Blend in Cheez Whiz.
Add the eggs (well beaten); mix gently until blended.
Turn into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover with crushed corn flakes; dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
May be made day before and baked when needed.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter nougat
directions: Mix together.
Form into balls and cover with chocolate.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with Pam.
Combine soup, butter, pepper, onion and cheese.
Gently mix in the potatoes and pour into pan or dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: texas delight
directions: Mix and pat flour, oleo and nuts in oblong pan or dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread on crust.
Mix pudding according to directions.
Put on top of cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: cajun fried chicken
directions: Place chicken in airtight container and pour hot sauce over. Marinate overnight.
Heat 1 inch oil in large skillet.
Put self-rising flour in shaker bag.
Add chicken to bag, a few pieces at a time.
Fry in hot (350°) oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chinese beef and rice
directions: Cook rice in hot oil over medium heat until golden brown.
Add salt, water, bouillon cubes and soy sauce.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover tightly and simmer 10 minutes more.
It may be necessary to add a little more water. All water should be absorbed at end of cooking time.
If not, remove cover and allow liquid to evaporate.

title: orange congealed salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for cake and bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until done (Bundt pan).

title: cranberry waldorf salad
directions: Grind cranberries and combine with marshmallows and sugar. Cover and chill overnight.
Add apple, walnuts and salt.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.
Serve in large bowl or individual lettuce cups.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and shake until well blended.

title: chicken-dressing-n-crock-pot
directions: Mix stuffing and butter.
Mix and heat in microwave the soups, water and broth.
Spray crock-pot with Pam.
Layer stuffing mix, then chicken, etc.
Pour soup mixture over last layer. Cook 6 to 8 hours on low.
Will make own gravy.
If doubled, use 1 bag regular and 1 bag herb stuffing.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix butter and peanut butter, then sugar.
Form in balls. Melt wax and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Drop balls in chocolate and put on wax paper until cool.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Mix and pour in greased/floured 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients.
Add spice.
Put in an 11 x 13-inch pan which has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Drizzle butter over top.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat mixture well and put in freezer.

title: heavenly macaroons
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove at once from cookie sheet.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco good.
Add sugar a little at a time, then add eggs, one at a time.
Then add flour and milk alternating.
Add vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Place in pound cake Bundt pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 325° in preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: short ribs a la francais
directions: Place ribs in kettle.
Add water to cover meat and later vegetables.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat.
Tie parsley, thyme, bay leaf, cloves and garlic in cheesecloth; add to kettle.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add carrots, turnips, leeks and onions; simmer 1 hour longer.
Add cabbage, celery and potatoes; cook for 45 minutes, until cabbage and potatoes are tender but not mushy.
Serve meat and vegetables on a large platter, along with fresh horseradish and coarse salt. Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs with a fork and add mashed banana.
Add lemon juice.
Blend with creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix quickly into banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan in a moderate 375° oven about 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: weight watchers muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Makes 4 large muffins or 6 small.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Place all ingredients except vanilla in a double boiler.
Mix thoroughly.
Cook, beating constantly with rotary or electric beater until mixture forms peaks, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Combine beef and onion in skillet; cook until meat is lightly browned.
Drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Stir in catsup and tomato sauce and heat thoroughly.
Turn into an 8-inch square or 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over meat.
Top with biscuits and bake until golden brown.
Cook at 350°.
Yields 12 servings.

title: pecan meal cake
directions: Beat egg whites stiff; add 1/4 cup sugar.
In another bowl, beat egg yolks with remaining 1 1/4 cups sugar for 5 minutes at medium speed.
Add flour, baking powder and salt that has been sifted together. Add vanilla.
Add 2 1/2 cups pecan meal.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in two 9-inch layers for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool thoroughly.
Ice with whipped cream (wine flavored).
Sprinkle pecan meal on top of whipped cream.

title: cavatini
directions: Brown ground beef.
Mix with cooked rigatoni, Ragu sauce, olives, mushrooms and pepperoni.
Pour into a baking dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch apple cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Beat eggs and add vanilla, oil and sugar.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Stir in nuts, apples and butterscotch morsels, reserving a few to sprinkle on top.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: beef barley soup
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add all ingredients into a large pot and simmer for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix next 3 ingredients with a little milk and put on combined salad ingredients, toss together.

title: ruth's hash
directions: Mix first six ingredients.
Put in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: earnest rohrer's pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Melt oleo. Add sugar, eggs, pineapple and coconut. Mix together. Put in an unbaked pie crust. Cook until golden brown.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Use a 4-quart plastic container with an airtight lid.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all the beans well and mix together.
Then stir in onion, celery and pepper.
Stir in dressing.
Let stand several hours or overnight to allow the flavor to blend.

title: apple yorkshire pudding
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch shallow pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon
evenly
over	butter.
Arrange apples over sugar. Sift flour	and salt together.
Beat eggs until light. Add flour and 1/2
cup
milk to eggs; beat until well blended. Gradually add last
cup
of
milk;
beat until smooth.
Gently pour over apples, bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.	Serve at once, cut in
squares (8 servings).
Especially good with warm syrup drizzled over top of squares.

title: aunt sib's fudge
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in large, heavy pan and boil until soft ball stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in remaining ingredients.
Stir until everything is dissolved.
Pour into greased 10 x 14-inch pan.
Cut when cool.

title: mama's old-timey icing
directions: Mix flour and milk in saucepan and cook until thick.
Cover and refrigerate.
In a mixing bowl, beat the shortening, sugar, vanilla and margarine until it gets thick and creamy.
Add chilled milk and flour that you refrigerated earlier and whip for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Spread over cooled cake.

title: bubble bread
directions: Melt Parkay.
Roll frozen rolls in Parkay, then in sugar and cinnamon.
Place in pan.
Pour any sugar or Parkay into pan.
Let rolls rise (according to package).
Pour whipping cream over rolls and pecans.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Bring to a boil pineapple and Jell-O and cool.
Add buttermilk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in dish and refrigerate.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Store cocoa mix in an airtight container.
To serve, place 1/3 cup mix in a cup.
Add 1 cup boiling water and stir well.
Yields 5 cups of mix.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil whole potatoes until tender when stuck with fork.
Cool and peel.
(Better if potatoes and hard-boiled eggs are cooled in refrigerator before peeling.)
Chop potatoes and eggs in small pieces; mix with rest of ingredients.
(Use more mayonnaise if needed.)
Put in casserole dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: cherry freeze salad
directions: Mix in large bowl, freeze.
Can add coconut or nuts.

title: oven chicken and dressing
directions: Dip chicken in flour; brown quickly.
Combine bread cubes, salt, pepper, sage, onions and oleo, using 1/2 cup soup.
Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Pile dressing in center.
Make gravy of drippings, using 2 tablespoons flour and enough water with remaining soup to make 2 cups.
Pour gravy over dressing and chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and knead until smooth.
Roll into small balls.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Chill overnight.
Easy and tastes real good.

title: seven layer taco dip
directions: In a medium bowl, blend season packet and refried beans. Spread the mixture on a large serving platter. Mix the sour cream and cream cheese in a medium bowl. Spread over the refried beans, then top with remaining ingredients. You can also use bell peppers or green onions and black olives.

title: macaroni-shrimp salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard, and salt.
Toss lightly.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Drain mushrooms and add to marinade.
Store in refrigerator at least 24 hours and as long as 2 weeks.
Remove from refrigerator at least one hour before serving.
Serve in bowl with toothpicks.

title: chicken fettucine alfredo
directions: Saute garlic in margarine, then stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Cook mixture 8 minutes or until thick.
Stir in cream cheese and cook 2 more minutes.
Add 1 cup parmesan cheese, stirring until melted.
Cook fettucini according to package directions; add chicken.
Pour the hot cheese sauce over the hot fettucini and chicken.
Toss well to coat.
Top mixture with the remaining 1/4 cup of parmesan cheese and sprinkle on some black pepper.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage and drain.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz.
Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Layer cabbage and crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heart-healthy spinach quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Use premade frozen pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: zucchini crisp
directions: Combine zucchini, water, sugar, lemon juice and cinnamon; boil 10 minutes.
Put in a 9-inch pie tin or 8 x 8-inch cake pan. Combine brown sugar, flour, baking powder and butter or oleo.
Put on top of mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baskin robbins pie
directions: Layer 1:
Melt oleo, mix flour and 1/2 cup chopped nuts and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.
Remove and cool completely.

title: spam casserole
directions: Cook rotini; drain.
In a skillet (while rotini is cooking), melt butter and saute onion and green pepper.
Add soup, ketchup, Spam and 2/3 of the cheese.
After rotini has been drained, combine all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Carrots, cauliflower, onion, tomatoes, cheese, broccoli.

title: toffee squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar, egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan; cook 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
As soon as it comes out of the oven, sprinkle pieces of candy bar and spread with a knife.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cut while warm.

title: bean soup
directions: In crock-pot, combine all ingredients, except ham, with 2 quarts water. Mix well. Then cover top completely with one layer of ham. Cook on high for 7 hours, stirring once or twice. Remove ham fat and bone before serving. It's great with cornbread.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (hot).
Mix sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon.
Toss lightly with apples.
Put apple mixture into a pastry-lined 9-inch pie pan.

title: garlic balls
directions: Roll dough into balls the size of a half dollar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Let stand 20 minutes or so.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until bottoms are golden. Do not cool.
Put warm, cooked garlic balls in a large bowl.
Season with salt and pepper, garlic powder, oregano, basil, parsley and olive oil. Stir frequently.
Add more seasoning to taste.

title: new brunswick stew
directions: Combine flour, salt and herbs in paper bag, shaking to mix well.
Place chicken pieces, one at a time.
Shake until coated. Pour oil into large pot which has tight fitting lid.
Heat oil, then add chicken pieces and cook until brown, then add onion and tomatoes.
Cook, covered, for 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Let cool, then remove meat from chicken bones and return meat to pot.
Add lima beans and corn, simmer for 30 minutes.
If needed, thicken with flour from sack and water.
Stir into stew and simmer for 10 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients and put in bottom of 9 x 11-inch dish. Top bean mixture with cheeses.
Mix taco seasoning mix and sour cream together and put on top of cheese layer.
Pour picante sauce over sour cream layer.
Put guacamole dip over picante. Cover with chopped green onions, chopped tomatoes and sliced black olives.

title: blender pancakes
directions: Blend milk and wheat on high for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add eggs, oil, honey, powder, soda and salt.
Bake on a 300° griddle (medium) for a very short time (until air bubbles pop).
Yummy, tummy filling whole wheat pancakes.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 3 greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: fabulous fudge
directions: Place evaporated milk and sugar in a large saucepan.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Let boil 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
While milk and sugar are boiling, place milk chocolate and semi sweet chocolate pieces, margarine and marshmallow cream in a large mixing bowl.
When milk mixture is ready, pour over chocolate mixture and stir until blended.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Chill until firm and cut and enjoy.
Yields 5 pounds.

title: cheese turkey and dressing
directions: Cook turkey breast in crock-pot overnight.
Spread breast and line a large pan with it.
Melt Velveeta, 1 1/4 cans cream of chicken soup and 1 1/2 cups turkey broth, stir until melted.
Pour mixture over the top of meat.
Next, in a large bowl crumble up biscuits and cornbread.
Add chopped eggs, onion, the rest of the soup and enough turkey broth to make moist.
Add sage and seasonings to taste.
Pour over meat and bake at 350° until dressing is done.

title: hayes house brisket
directions: Line baking pan with foil.
Place brisket in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients to make a marinade and pour over brisket. Fold foil up to seal and refrigerate and let stand overnight.
Do not reopen. Bake for 5 hours at 300°.
Finished brisket will be tender to a fork and melt in your mouth delicious.

title: muffin mix
directions: Melt shortening in boiling water.
Combine all dry ingredients in very large bowl or roasting pan.
Add sour milk, eggs and shortening/water mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Store in an ice cream pail in the refrigerator.
Keeps up to six weeks.
Makes 50 muffins.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage into small pieces, not into patties.
Drain and add to scrambled eggs mixing in cheese until melted.
Spread tortillas with butter and heat in microwave.
Fill tortillas with mixture and fold.
Ready to serve.

title: garlic potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes with water to cover.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain and let stand until cool.

title: creamed chicken and biscuits
directions: In saucepan melt margarine.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Add broth and cook until thickened like gravy.
Stir in about 1 cup cooked chicken pieces and continue heating.
Serve over biscuits. (This is a good way to use leftover chicken or turkey "scraps.")

title: mama's vegetable soup
directions: This makes a large pot of soup!

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt the butter.
Add onion and ground beef; brown beef well.
Remove from heat; drain off fat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Spread beef mixture over pie crust. Spread cheese over beef mixture.

title: italian spinach with egg
directions: *I usually use Egg Beaters to cut down on cholesterol.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt oleo.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add soups and shrimp; heat over low fire, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are done, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet.
Drain grease.
Layer meat and sliced potatoes in casserole dish.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over potatoes and meat.
Can also add water chestnuts, English peas, corn or any vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes until potatoes are tender.
Add cheese on top and brown.
Can be made day before and refrigerated.

title: baked cheese torte
directions: Mix crushed graham crackers with 1/4 cup sugar and 1/3 cup butter.
Set aside 3/4 cup to sprinkle over top.
Press remainder of crumbs into 10-inch spring-form pan, lining bottom and sides. Beat eggs and 1 cup sugar until light; add salt, lemon juice and rind, milk, cheese and flour and beat.
Put cottage cheese through potato ricer so it is smooth.
Pour into lined pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until center is set.
Turn off heat.
Let cool in oven 1 hour with door open.

title: chicken chili
directions: Simmer chicken in water until tender.
Cut into cubes; reserve broth.
Heat oil; saute onions and garlic.
Add chilies and spices; saute for 2 minutes.
Add chicken and cheese; heat until well blended.

title: potatoes ala yorba
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Scrub potatoes cooked with skin on. Cool and peel potatoes. Grate and shred potatoes.

Set aside. Heat 1/4 cup butter with soup. Add chives, onion salt, sour cream and cheese. Mix well. Season to taste. Add potatoes. Spray casserole dish in oil. Add mixture. Melt 2 tablespoons of butter and mix with crushed cornflakes. Sprinkle on top of potatoes. Bake 45 minutes.

title: uncle mike horn's spaghetti and meat delight
directions: Brown sausage, beef and ham.
Cook bacon crisp.
Mix in onion. Drain off liquid.
Add the drained pineapple.
Mix meat and onion together with Prego and garlic.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Melt margarine in large pan.
Saute celery, onion and garlic until tender.
Add tomatoes and stir.
Add potatoes and carrots. Cook, covered, over medium heat until partially cooked.
Add green beans, zucchini, green pepper and peas.
Season.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Dip in buttermilk.
Roll in flour. For extra crusty chicken, repeat.
Fry in medium-hot oil just to brown, turning once.
Reduce heat and cook on medium-low heat for 10 minutes on each side or until juice runs clear.
Don't turn often to keep crust from coming off.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening.
Do not use beaters.
Mix like pie crumbs in a large bowl.
Save 1 cup of crumbs for top of cake.
In another bowl, mix molasses, hot water and baking soda. Add to crumbs.
Stir and put into a large greased and floured pan. Top with 1 cup of reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Boil the potatoes until barely tender.
Cool and peel them. Cut into chunks, you should have 5 to 6 cups of potato chunks.
Mix cottage cheese, sour cream and garlic.
Add salt, pepper and onion in a large bowl.
Add potato chunks.
Stir to coat potatoes then pour into a large, flat casserole.
Top with cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: perfect wedding punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together very good except ginger ale. Divide punch into 2 containers (each container fills a punch bowl) and freeze overnight. Take out of freezer 4 hours before using. Slush (with an old-fashioned potato masher) and add 1 1/2 large bottles ginger ale to each container of punch. Serves 50 people.

title: dilly dip
directions: Mix together and serve with vegetables.
Delicious!

title: luscious lime whip
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl with Cool Whip on top.
Fold all ingredients together.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Break noodles in small pieces and cook according to directions on box.
Drain.
Place noodles in a buttered casserole dish; top with asparagus.
Mix mushroom soup and a little juice from asparagus or milk.
Pour over asparagus and noodles.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: french peasant soup
directions: Wash beans.
Combine with 1 quart water in an 8-quart kettle. Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Simmer beans until tender, 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Cook bacon.
Add to beans.
Cook onion slices in bacon fat until slightly browned on both sides.
Add to beans along with bacon fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except sausage.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Add sausage and continue cooking until all vegetables are tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove sausage.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix beans, onions and parsley in large bowl.
Mix Italian dressing, sugar and garlic.
Pour over salad and toss.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally, at least 3 hours.
Just before serving, remove to lettuce lined salad bowl with slotted spoon. Makes 5 or 6 servings.

title: lemon rice stuffing for fish
directions: Saute celery, oil, water, lemon ring and onion.
Add seasonings.
Then add rice, sour cream and diced lemon.
Mix and stuff fish.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine pineapple and pudding mix with spoon.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: steamed red potatoes with dill butter
directions: In a small bowl, cream together the butter, dill, garlic salt and pepper to taste.
In steamer, steam potatoes, covered, for 12 to 14 minutes, until tender.
Slice them and serve topped with the dill butter.
Serves 4.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until tender.
Drain and cool. In bowl alternate carrots, pepper and onion.
Combine marinade ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: quick and easy watermelon pie
directions: Fold together milk and topping.
Add lime juice.
Fold in watermelon balls, reserving about 5 balls for garnish.
Place in freezer for at least 8 hours or until mixture freezes.

title: fantasy fudge cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream the margarine. Add sugar and mix well. Add eggs, vanilla and cocoa.
Mix well. Stir in flour, soda and salt. Add chocolate chips, white chocolate and nuts. Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cookies will be soft and appear to be undercooked.
Don't overbake.
Chewy and good.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix chopped pecan pieces and crushed vanilla wafers together. Add milk, red cherries and coconut. Pack mixture by hand in dish or glass loaf pan. Store in refrigerator.

title: can't fail fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Boil exactly 9 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients, stir and pour into a large, greased pan. Cool and cut into squares.

title: microwave choco-nut candy crunch
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, melt almond bark, peanut butter and chocolate chips on 80% powder for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir and microwave 1 1/2 minutes longer.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Let hash browns thaw (can use real potatoes).
Mix sour cream and soup.
Add onions and pour over hash browns.
Add cheese. Crush and sprinkle cereal on top and back.	Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cover the first 20 minutes.
Grease pan 8 x 13.

title: elderberry doughnuts
directions: Soak elderberries in milk for 48 hours in refrigerator.
Add sugar to egg yolk and beat until light.
Stir in sugar and yolk mixture into milk and berries.
Add soda, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Mix.
Add to berry mixture.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot cooking oil (360°) and deep fry until golden brown, turning occasionally.
Makes 20.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 3 minutes.
Chop into bite sized pieces.
Add onion, eggs, olives and a generous amount of mayonnaise (enough to coat well).
Serves 6.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix potatoes and powdered sugar.
Stir in coconut, salt and vanilla.
Blend well.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Pour on top of candy.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Cook ingredients for 2 1/2 minutes.
Add about 1/2 jar of peanut butter.
Beat until smooth and spread on cake.

title: broccoli jennifer
directions: Mix all ingredients except the cracker crumbs and butter. Place in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter and cover with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly (about 45 minutes). Serves 6 to 8.

title: warm vegetable salad with mustard dressing
directions: Dressing:
Combine mustard, vinegar, water, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Whisk in oil.
Set aside.

title: tasty pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides in margarine. Mix in remaining ingredients. Turn into lightly greased casserole or 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan. Place chops and drippings on top of rice mixture. Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and drain.
Saute onion in frying pan.
Add 1/4 cup water and rice.
Saute for 3 or 4 minutes.
Quarter and core cabbage.
Chop coarsely.
Mix tomato soup with remaining 1 cup water.
Mix rice and onion mix, salt and pepper with hamburger. Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with cooking spray.
Put 1/4 cup soup mixture on bottom of pan.
Layer hamburger and cabbage until all is used.
Top with remaining soup mix.
Spoon ketchup on top. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: bacon cheese spread
directions: *Can use 2 pieces crumbled bacon.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Soak raisins in boiling water; cool.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add raisins.
Use a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: platillo
directions: For best results, in a food processor, finely chop onion, peppers, garlic, ham steak and chorizos.
Mix with tomato sauce, salt, pepper and small amount of olive oil.
Heat in skillet. Cook 1 pound angel hair pasta; drain and mix with meat mixture.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Slice onions into rings 5/8-inch thick.
Blanch them for 2 minutes and drain.
Combine the melted butter, crushed crackers and cheese.
Layer 1/3 of the onions in the bottom of a large, rectangular pan.
Sprinkle them with 1/3 of the cracker mixture. Repeat the layers two more times.
Sprinkle with the milk.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Spread enough beans to cover bottom of a platter or plate. Sprinkle taco seasoning over beans.
Layer the remaining ingredients. Serve with Doritos.

title: carrot coins
directions: Slice carrots thin, or use small carrots as they come from the package.
Cook in boiling salted water for 10 minutes; drain. Combine all other ingredients; bring to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add drained carrots; cook 10 minutes.
Cool. Refrigerate overnight before serving.
Keeps well.

title: mom's fresh apple cake
directions: With fork, stir the sugar into the oil.
Beat the eggs and add to sugar mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add to other ingredients.
Add vanilla; mix.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: layered dinner salad
directions: Drain tomatoes thoroughly, reserving 2 tablespoons of juice. Layer ingredients in a large salad bowl (clear glass if possible) as follows:
lettuce, mushrooms, drained tomatoes, chicken, onion, peas and cucumbers.
Combine mayonnaise with tomato juice, seasoned salt, tarragon and pepper.
Blend well.
Spread over top of salad.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with hard-boiled eggs (sliced) and parsley.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Mix together pizza sauce and spaghetti sauce. Cook hamburger; add to sauce. Layer in 5-quart crock-pot: noodles, meat sauce, onions, green peppers, cheese and pepperoni. Finish with cheese on the top. Cook on low heat about 4 hours until cheese is melted.

title: martha's quick chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Blend together dry and liquid ingredients.
Pour into a layer or spring-form pan prepared for a moist cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool thoroughly for neat removal.
Top with whipped cream, powdered sugar or frosting.

title: 9 layer lettuce salad
directions: Tear up 1 large head of lettuce into bite size pieces and lay into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the following on top: peas, celery, green pepper, onion, eggs and bacon pieces.
Combine sugar and Miracle Whip.
Frost top of layered salad with this.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Boil dates and prunes in1 cup water for 3 minutes.
Add margarine and
raisins
and
let cool.
Mix flour, soda, salt, eggs, nuts, spice and vanilla.
Add to fruit mixture.
Stir to blend.
Pour
in
baking
dish.
Bake
for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: In a large bowl beat milk, pudding and water.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: fluffy sour cream pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Combine sour cream and baking soda. Stir into egg yolks.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir into sour cream mixture.
Add oleo and beat 30 seconds using medium speed.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold whites into batter.

title: potatoes for a crowd
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until golden brown on top.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine and mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put frozen rolls in Bundt pan and spread cooked pudding on top. Melt oleo and add brown sugar and cinnamon; pour over rolls and let set until it doubles in bulk. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: red cabbage with apples
directions: Wash cabbage; cut as for coleslaw. Peel and chop apples. Heat fat in large saucepan and cook apple and onion gently 3 to 4 minutes. Add water, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, cloves, bay leaf and lemon juice. Stir; bring to boil. Add cabbage; mix well. Cover; simmer 45 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle flour over top. Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Mix well and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: yuletime punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a punch bowl.
Makes 3 quarts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon.
In another bowl, add sugar, oil, water, eggs and pumpkin; mix well. Combine with dry ingredients and add nuts.
Mix until smooth. Grease pans well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for loaf pans, 25 minutes for cake pans or 30 minutes for muffin pans.
Frost with powdered sugar.
Enjoy!

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Spread ground beef on bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Salt and pepper to taste, then layer potatoes followed by onions. Put cream of mushroom soup on top of onions and then the can of cream of celery soup.
Top with cheese, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast and let cool.
Cut in bite-size pieces. Spray a 9 x 13-inch dish with Pam.
Layer bottom of dish with 1/2 of dressing mix then layer 1/2 of chicken.
Combine soups, broth and Stove Top seasonings and pour 1/2 over chicken.
Repeat.
Spot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Blend together cocoa and sugar. Add melted butter, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip when cool.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, margarine, sugars and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and soda, beat until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 50 minutes.
Cool 15 to 20 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: snackin' granola bars
directions: Toast oats in ungreased large shallow pan in moderate 350° oven until hot.
Combine toasted oats with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Press firmly into well-greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch* jellyroll pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 15 minutes. Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all
ingredients
except
corn
and
butter and mix well. Add corn
and mix in.
Pour into casserole and dot with butter. Bake at 350° until solid and top is nicely browned.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix.
Put on sliced bread.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°.

title: rouladen(german)
directions: Pound roast slices in flour.
Put one slice of onion (or pearl onions) and 1/4 or 1/2 slice of bacon in each slice.
Roll the meat up and secure with toothpicks.
In an electric frypan, place 2 tablespoons oil and brown meat on all sides.
Remove the meat and place on a skewer.
Add flour to drippings; brown and add 1 cup water.
Put beef back in this gravy.
Simmer for at least 1 hour.

title: easy no peek chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees spray 9X13 glass pan with nonstick spray. Place chicken in pan with nonstick spray. Place chicken in pan. Combine rest of ingredients and pour
over chicken. Cover with foil and bake 2 1/2 hours. No Peeking!

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Place cleaned shrimp in the bottom of a baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over shrimp and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: school house rolls
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 3 ingredients and let mixture cool a little.
Then, in a small bowl, mix 5 Tbsp. yeast with 2 c. warm water.
Add yeast mixture to sugar, oil, and water mixture in large bowl.
Add 1/2 c. milk and 1 1/2 tsp. salt.
Gradually add 3-4 lb. plain flour until dough is firm.
Knead until mixed.
Cut dough in half.
Roll out on lightly floured surface and cut out with biscuit cutter.
Place rolls on lightly greased baking sheets.
Cover sheets loosely with plastic wrap.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.
Makes about 50 rolls.

title: crumbly peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and nutmeg together.
Cut in butter. Sprinkle 1/2 of this mixture on bottom of crust.
Arrange peaches on top, then cover with remaining mixture.
Add water.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for an additional 30 minutes.

title: salmon log spread
directions: Drain salmon.
Combine salmon, cheese, lemon juice, grated onion, horseradish and salt.
Shape into 2 logs.
Chill.
Roll logs in pecans and parsley.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Slice and serve on crackers.

title: slow-cooked chili
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese in slow cooker. Cover. Cook on low 8 to 10 hours. Ladle chili into individual bowls and top with cheese just before serving.

title: texas hash browns
directions: Mix ingredients and put in greased 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease bottom only of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over bottom. Combine strawberries and gelatin and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, combine rest of the ingredients; blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat three minutes at medium speed.
Pour batter over marshmallows.
Pour strawberry mixture evenly over batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until golden brown and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix at lowest speed the juice, pudding and food coloring. Fold in marshmallows and pineapple.
Serves 10.

title: mock lasagna
directions: Mix together cream cheese, onion and sour cream (can be done in food processor).
Brown ground beef.
Add Ragu and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Wash and sort navy beans.
Soak in water overnight in slow cooker pot.
When ready to cook, add remaining ingredients and cook 6 hour on setting number 3.
Remove ham bone and cut off meat.
Dice and return to soup.
Season to taste with additional salt and pepper, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
If desired, the process may be reversed.
Soak the beans during the day and cook the soup overnight.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water to dissolve.
Add cold water and the juice from the can of pineapple chunks.
Add cranberries and the pineapple chunks and put in refrigerator to set.

title: shortbread
directions: Mix.
Shape into balls and flatten to 1/2-inch thick.
Prick with a fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crispy cajun bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix oil, dip mix and seasoning blend in a small dish; drizzle over bread shells.
Bake until hot, 6 to 8 minutes.
To serve, cut in wedges.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and baking powder.
Mix in vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons into bowl of crushed cornflakes.
Roll dough until coated with cornflakes.
Flatten on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit well in separate containers.
Dice apples (peel or not, as desired).
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: "even if you don't like broccoli" casserole
directions: Mix broccoli and soup together.
Prepare stuffing with half the water that is called for on stuffing box.
Alternate layers of broccoli-soup mixture, stuffing, sour cream and cheese (except on top).
Use square baking dish (9 x 9-inch).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add top layer of cheese and bake for 5 minutes longer.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Stir egg and milk mixture into flour mixture smoothly.
Pour grease off roast except 1/2-inch.
Remove roast and put pudding in pan, having it about 1/2-inch thick.
Bake.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Heat pineapple and jello until jello is dissolved.
Stir while this is heating; cool.
Add buttermilk; mix.
Fold in Cool Whip. Chill overnight.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemon and milk until creamy.
Pour in pie shell and refrigerate.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Brown meat.
Drain off excess fat.
Saute onions, garlic and bell pepper in fat from the meat.
Add your meat and beans and 8 to 10 cups of water.
Season to taste.
Boil gently, stirring occasionally for 1 hour.
Add bay leaf.
Cook for 1/2 to 1 hour longer or until beans are tender.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Grate cheese and mix with oleo.
Sift flour, salt and pepper together.
Blend cheese and oleo mixture with sifted dry ingredients (makes firm dough).
Roll into small balls about the size of a walnut.
Press down thin; bake 10 minutes at 450°. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Top with pecan half.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish and cover with foil.
Bake in a 400°
oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serve with rice.

title: chocolate peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over boiling water. Remove from heat.
Add Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk and peanuts or raisins and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered baking sheet or plate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix peanut butter, sugar and egg. Spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Place kiss on top of hot cookie.
Allow to cool.
Enjoy!

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg yolks and vanilla thoroughly. Measure flour by dipping method or sifting.
Blend together flour and salt; stir in.
Roll dough into balls, 1 teaspoon per ball. Beat egg whites slightly with fork.
Dip balls in egg whites. Roll in nuts.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Press your thumbprint in center of cookie to make an indentation. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Fill with confectioners sugar icing, tinted in various colors.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a skillet with a lid; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, basil and thyme and toss gently.
Cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve immediately.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large mixer bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in 3 greased and floured cake pans at 350° until done.

title: cholya saalan
directions: Clean, wash, and dry the catfish; sprinkle with salt and set aside.

title: elegant potato casserole
directions: Grate or slice cooled potatoes. Melt 1/4 c. of the butter in the soup. Cool and blend in sour cream. Add potatoes, green onions and 1 c. of the grated cheese to the mixture, adding salt and pepper to taste. Put into casserole dish(es). Dot with remaining butter and cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes two nice casseroles and can be prepared and frozen and then baked when ready to serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together; roll into small balls.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: ground beef soup
directions: Brown beef thoroughly and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 hours.
Low in fat.
Low in calories.
High in fiber. Freezes well.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine soda, water and vanilla and set aside.
Place sugar, water and corn syrup in a deep 3-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Stir to blend.
Heat sugar mix, uncovered, on Full power for 20 minutes or until candy thermometer reaches 240° (soft ball stage).
Do not cook with thermometer in oven or use temperature probe.
Stir in butter until melted.
Add peanuts and cook, uncovered, on Full power for 12 minutes or until candy thermometer reaches 300° (hard ball stage).
Stir occasionally with wooden spoon.
Grease two cookie sheets.
Stir soda, water and vanilla mix into hot candy mixture.
Quickly pour onto prepared cookie sheets and spread to 1/4-inch thickness.
When cool, break into pieces and enjoy.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, milk, butter (1/2 cup) and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into casserole dish.
Mix sugar, butter, flour and nuts; put on top of casserole.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: rice imperial
directions: Combine rice and 1 1/2 cups milk in a saucepan; cook uncovered over medium heat, stirring frequently for about 20 minutes or until all milk is absorbed.
Soften gelatin in mandarin juice, stir in mandarin peel.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and the remaining 1/2 cup milk, 1/4 teaspoon salt and slightly beaten egg yolks in a 2 1/2- quart saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved and mixture coats a spoon.
Add gelatin mixture and rice.
Continue cooking, stirring constantly until gelatin is dissolved and mixture well blended.
Cool, then chill.

title: aunt deb's chili
directions: Brown sausage and equal amount of ground beef; set aside to drain.
In skillet, place onions, jalapenos, bell peppers, chili powder, sage, oregano, cayenne pepper, cocoa, salt, pepper, cinnamon and vinegar.
Simmer until onions are clear then stir in meats.
Put tomatoes, beans and water into slow cooker pot and add all other ingredients when slow boil occurs.
Let simmer at least 1 hour.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar and spices.
Dissolve 1 teaspoon of soda in buttermilk and add to dry ingredients.
Add Wesson oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add prunes, pecans and vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: karo crazy crunch
directions: Mix corn and nuts
in large pan.
Cook sugar, margarine and syrup in saucepan
over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mix turns to a
light
caramel color.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour over
corn and nuts.
Mix well to coat. Spread to dry.
When	cool,
break
apart.
Store
in
tightly covered container.	Makes about 2 pounds.

title: fruit balls
directions: Put brown sugar, margarine, chopped nuts and dates in boiler and cook for about 6 minutes, stirring constantly, until hot. Cool about 15 minutes and then add Rice Krispies and nuts. Roll into balls and drop into confectioners sugar. Makes about 100 small balls.

title: peach kuchen(dessert)
directions: Mix until crumbly the margarine, cake mix and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: hawaiian beans
directions: Drain beans. Fry bacon and onions, draining off fat. Add to beans. Add remaining ingredients, mixing well. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spiced pumpkin bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine the dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine the eggs, pumpkin, oil and water; mix well.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into three greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.

title: muffuletta bread
directions: Prepare roll mix as directed on package.
Place dough onto greased pizza pan or cookie sheet; press dough to a 12-inch circle.
Grease top with cooking oil; cover with plastic wrap. Let rise until double in bulk, about 30 minutes.

title: grandma bigler's crumb cake
directions: Mix the first three ingredients and take out 1/2 cup for crumbs.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Spread reserved crumbs on top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken pieces thoroughly and dry with paper towels. Crush cereal very fine.
Stir the thyme into the crumbs.
Pour the milk into a shallow bowl and dissolve the salt in it.
Dip the chicken pieces one at a time into the milk, then roll in the crumbs to coat completely.
Place in baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until browned and tender when pricked with a fork.

title: rock candy
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients
to a boil in a 3-quart heavy pot to 305°.
Remove from heat and add food coloring and 1/2 bottle of extract (any flavor).
Mix well.
Pour into sprayed long cake pan.
Cut with scissors into small pieces and drop them into powdered sugar.
Let cool before placing into bag or jar for storage.

title: company chicken
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Wrap bacon around chicken. Line the bottom of the pan with dried beef.
Pepper the chicken liberally, but do not salt.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over chicken and dried beef mixture.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.
Good with Birds Eye green beans with almonds.

title: sliced sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Blanch in boiling water and the juice of lemon.
Cool.
Lay out the bottom crust in pie tin.
Mix together the sugars, salt and cinnamon.
Layer the potatoes with the sugar mixture.
Dot each layer as you go with butter.
Drizzle the top layer with vanilla.
Top with remaining crust.
Crimp and brush with milk.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Best if served warm.

title: salmon party ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans and parsley.
Chill to handle.
Roll in mixture of pecans and parsley.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: spinach pinwheels
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon until done but not crisp; drain on paper towels.
Score steak by making shallow cuts at 1-inch intervals diagonally across steak in a diamond pattern.
Repeat on second side.
With a meat mallet, pound steak into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Arrange bacon lengthwise on steak.
Spread spinach over bacon.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Roll meat from a short side (like a jelly roll). Secure with toothpicks at 1-inch intervals, starting 1/2 inch from end.
Grill for a minimum of 20 minutes.
Serve with a Hollandaise Sauce.

title: fat-free banana muffins
directions: Spray muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine flours, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon and stir thoroughly.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites lightly with a wire whisk or fork.
Stir in mashed banana, milk and corn syrup.
Add flour mixture and stir until well blended.
Spoon into prepared muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until firm to touch.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes, then remove and cool on a wire rack.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Mix in sour cream and dry ingredients, alternating. Beat egg whites; fold into batter.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fajitas
directions: Wrap flour tortillas in foil; warm in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have all cheeses at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients together except nuts.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped nuts. Chill.

title: gumdrop bars
directions: Beat eggs with water until light.
Add sugar and mix well.
Use a small amount of flour to dust gumdrops and nuts.
Add sifted dry ingredients to egg mixture, mix and stir in gumdrops and nuts. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 24 minutes.
While warm, frost with Orange Butter Frosting.
Cut in squares or bars.

title: picnic potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with skins for 20 minutes.
Cool; peel and shred in a bowl.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in soup and sour cream; heat until well blended.
Mix potatoes with cheese, then add soup mixture.
Pour into greased baking pan and refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients except pecans.
Pour into pie shells and sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350°.

title: salmon or halibut
directions: Lay steaks in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
Remove and drain off liquid.
Spread with sour cream.
Sprinkle with dill weed.
Bake 6 minutes more and serve.

title: pralines
directions: Cook ingredients to soft ball.
Add 1 1/2 to 2 cups whole pecans.
Stir until mixture starts to sugar, but is not yet sugared.
Now work quickly.
Spoon onto aluminum foil to cool in 2-inch diameter piles.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix as box reads; cool.
Poke holes all in it.
Mix coconut cream and Eagle Brand together.
Pour all in holes until all is used.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle coconut over Cool Whip.

title: sinful oreo delight
directions: Spread ice cream on top of cookie mixture.
Put in freezer. Melt chocolate, salt, butter, milk and sugar on stove for 4 or 5 minutes.
Set off to cool.
Add vanilla; pour on top of ice cream. Freeze.

title: aunt annie's golden puffs
directions: Mix all together.
Take small teaspoon of dough; mix and fry in oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix margarine, mustard and seeds on low heat.
Cool and refrigerate until margarine hardens.
Slice rolls into halves a pack at a time with a long knife.
Spread mustard sauce on both sides of rolls.
Cut beef into squares and cheese into squares. Return top half of rolls and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: candied potatoes
directions: Bring water, sugar and margarine to a boil.
Mix flavoring and cornstarch with enough water to make a paste.
Stir into other mixture as it boils.
Pour over drained potatoes.
Heat slowly for a few minutes.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Put 1 1/2 cups sugar with fruit and boil 5 minutes.
Add remaining sugar and boil 10 to 15 minutes. A watery fruit must be cooked longer. Pour into earthenware jar, wide mouth glass jar or ceramic jar.

title: sweet tater pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter, egg yolks, 1 cup of sugar, salt and spice.
Mix well.
Add milk, blending well.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff.
Fold egg whites into potato mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 350° for 30 minutes. When cool, serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel and seed avocados.
In a bowl, mash avocados with lime juice and salt.
Add onions, chilies and tomatoes.
Mix thoroughly. Cover and chill.
Makes approximately 3 cups.
Serve with chips, crackers or raw vegetables.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar, cornstarch and food coloring until it comes to boil.
Add Jell-O; cool.
Pour in baked pie shell with fresh strawberries.
Let cool for 5 to 6 hours.

title: sweet & spicy roasted pork and apples
directions: Position rack in center of oven, preheat to 425 degrees. Combine 2 tablespoons sugar, chili powder, salt.
Rub this mixture over pork loin.
Place on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Roast 20 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 375 degrees, bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Let stand 10 minutes before carving. Meanwhile, coat jellyroll pan with cooking spray, in pan toss apples, onion with tablespoon vinegar, oil, cinnamon and remaining sugar.
Place in oven 30 minutes before pork is done.
Cook until golden, stirring every 10 minutes.
In pot over high heat, combine juice, broth, thyme, and remaining vinegar.
Cover, bring to boil and uncover, bring to boil 30 more minutes.
Transfer pork and apples to platter.
Add pan drippings to juice mixture, whisk in butter, pour over meat.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins and water 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain raisin liquid and add enough water to make 1/2 cup.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in raisin liquid.
Blend dry ingredients and stir in.
Add oats, raisins and nuts.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°, until lightly browned.

title: 7 day sweet pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers thoroughly.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 24 hours and drain well.
Repeat each day for 4 days, using fresh boiling water each day.
On the 5th day, cut cucumbers into desired pieces.
Combine sugar, salt, vinegar and spices.
Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain well.
Bring same syrup to a boil and cover cucumbers.
Repeat on 6th day.
On 7th day, drain and again bring syrup to a boil.
Add cucumbers; bring to a boiling point and put into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
First few days they look like they will spoil, but they will become very crisp.

title: speedy vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Remove fat as desired.
Add water, vegetables and other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Turn to low heat.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes or until tasty.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, pour melted butter. Add other ingredients, one by one.
Sprinkle crumbs over melted butter, nuts over crumbs, chocolate over nuts, coconut over chocolate and condensed milk over top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until lightly brown.
Cool 15 minutes before cutting into bars.

title: aunt geraldine's caramel icing
directions: Put all together; stir over low-medium heat until it boils. Cook for 5 minutes.
Set off; beat.

title: strawberry-rhubarb cobbler
directions: Cook rhubarb until tender.
Add strawberries, sugar and flour and mix well.
Pour into crust.
Cover with top crust and fold over bottom crust.
Dot with margarine and sprinkle lightly with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: angel cookies
directions: Cream oleo and shortening.
Add sugars and egg, then add dry ingredients.
Roll in small balls.
Dip in water, then in sugar and place on ungreased cookie pan.
Press down in center with thumb.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese and green chile sandwich
directions: Put one piece of cheese on each piece of bread.
Then add chiles and close sandwich. Wrap with aluminum foil; heat in 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: taco soup
directions: Dump all together; do not drain beans,	etc.
Simmer on low for 2 hours.
Top bowls with cheese,
chips, etc. whatever you desire.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Cream butter and peanut butter together.
Gradually add sugar and mix well.
Add unbeaten egg and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients gradually; mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls, using a round teaspoon for each. Roll in sugar and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and press kiss firmly into cookies. Bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs, milk, vanilla, melted margarine, pecans and coconut; mix well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery pieces in boiling water until slightly tender. Drain thoroughly.
Pour into mixing bowl.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup soft bread crumbs, 1/4 cup slivered almonds tossed in 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Combine mayonnaise mixture with broccoli flowerets, onion and cheese.
Sprinkle bacon on top; let sit overnight before serving.

title: apple kuchen(so good and simple)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into cake mix (dry) until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly in ungreased baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch), building up slight edges.
Bake 10 minutes. Arrange apple slices on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle on apples.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Cover vegetables with salt and let stand for 1 hour. Do not drain. In a bowl, combine sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed; stir until sugar is dissolved. Add mixture to vegetables and stir. Will keep for several weeks in a Tupperware container.

title: shower punch for 50
directions: Mix sugar and water together and boil for 5 minutes; set aside to cool.
Mix other ingredients together and pour into cooled sugar water (except the 7-Up).
Put in freezer until slushy.
Add 7-Up and serve.
This may not serve 50 people because it's so good they will want more than 1 serving.

title: seafood sauce
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and parsley; add chili sauce, green onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Makes 1 cup.

title: yams hawaiian style
directions: Slice yams 1/2-inch thick.
Combine with pineapple, butter, sugar and cinnamon in a 2-quart casserole.
Microwave at High for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Combine 1/2 cup chopped pecans and a 1/4 cup light brown sugar.
Sprinkle on top and microwave at High for 2 to 4 minutes.
If dish is not hot or topping has not melted after 2 minutes, rotate dish 1/4 turn before continuing to microwave.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well, oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to liquid.
Mix.
Add carrots and pecans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: gooey burgers
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add other ingredients, except cheese. Spoon onto buns and top with cheese.
Wrap each individually in foil and bake at 350° until the cheese melts (5 to 10 minutes).

title: raisin praline bars
directions: Blend the butter, brown sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg. Stir in raisins and pecans.
Resift the sifted flour with the baking powder and salt into raisin mixture. Blend thoroughly.
Turn into greased and floured 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Spread dough evenly.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out and cut into squares.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix salad dressing, mustard, pickle relish, eggs, celery, onion and potatoes.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Wash squash well.
Cut through the middle.
Scoop out pulp. Trim bottom of each cup just enough so that it will set upright. Melt margarine.
Coat inside of squash with it.
Add applesauce and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Place in baking dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until squash is tender.
Serves 4 people.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco.
Add all eggs, slightly beaten.
Add flour and milk (starting and ending with flour).
Add flavoring and baking powder.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in tube cake pan.

title: pink smoothie salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add applesauce and bananas; mix well and refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Boil water, sugar and cornstarch until clear.
Add peach jello.
Cook until thick; cool.
Add fruit.
Pour into graham cracker crust and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix with 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly. Save 1 cup oil for top.
Pat remaining mixture lightly in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon pie
directions: Juice the lemons and grate the rinds;
discard the rest of the lemons.

title: apple curry pork chops
directions: Saute pork chops in large Teflon skillet (medium hot pan, so no fat needed).
Brown on both sides.
Combine in bowl the applesauce, wine, raisins, onion, lemon rind, curry and ginger; pour over pork chops in skillet.
Cover; turn heat low.
Cook for 45 minutes, or until tender.
Remove meat; reduce sauce.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together in a bowl first, then add the last 3 ingredients and knead.
Roll out pie shell.

title: best homemade chili
directions: Cook beef, garlic, onion and green pepper in a heavy skillet over medium-high heat, stirring frequently to break up meat.
Cook until onion is soft and meat has lost its pink color.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer the chili for 45 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: patsy lawton's turtles
directions: Melt caramels and canned milk in double boiler over low heat. Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet sprayed well with Pam.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour; can leave overnight.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: 100 cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
With an electric mixer, mix margarine, brown sugar, white sugar, salad oil, egg and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, sift together the salt, baking soda, cream of tartar and flour.
Once the margarine-sugar mixture is mixed and creamy, add the sifted dry ingredients using a large spoon to mix together.
With a teaspoon, drop dough onto cookie sheet and bake for 12 minutes.

title: honey whole wheat bread or dinner rolls
directions: Note:
Be careful not to kill yeast with water hotter than 115°.
If in doubt, use a thermometer to check.

title: carol's baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off any fat drippings. Cook bacon.
Crumble and add to meat mixture.
Slightly drain pork and beans and add to meat mixture.
Add catsup, mustard and brown sugar.
Simmer, uncovered.
Mixture will candy in approximately 20 minutes.

title: beef skillet fiesta
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add tomato paste, corn, chili powder and oil.
Cook until hot, boiling.
Add rice and cover for 5 minutes or until rice is done.

title: angel cake
directions: Prepare cake by cutting in half, using horizontal cut at mid-range, thereby, creating 2 layers of cake.
Combine in medium mixing bowl, Cool Whip and well drained pineapple chunks.
Frost cake layers, as a 2-layer cake, with mixture accordingly. Refrigerate until served.

title: party candy
directions: Sift sugar into a large pan (dishpan size).
Add softened butter and condensed milk to sugar.
When thoroughly mixed, add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Shape into balls and chill in refrigerator.

title: spanish chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Crush tortilla chips and layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chicken.
Mix soup, chiles and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Daddy's favorite!

title: cauliflower-pea casserole
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets and cook in a small amount of unsalted boiling water for 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain well and place with peas in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Set aside.
Saute almonds and curry powder in 1 tablespoon butter.
Cook, stirring constantly, until almonds are browned.
Set aside.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons butter and flour in heavy saucepan and stir until smooth.
Gradually stir in sour cream.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until well heated.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Pour over cauliflower mixture.
Sprinkle almonds on top. Let stand for 30 minutes, then bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: million dollar pound cake
directions: Combine
sugar
and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one
at
a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour
to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after
each addition.
Stir
in
flavoring.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and
40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack to cool completely.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Press into a 9 X 13 X 2 inch baking dish.
Bake at 350 for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken cutlets supreme
directions: Dip cutlets in egg and then bread crumbs. Fry cutlets to a light golden brown.
Mix the 2 cans of soup with 1 can of milk and mix in blender.
Arrange cutlets in a casserole dish.
Cover with soup mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Place chicken in bottom of a 9 x 13 dish.
Mix soups, butter and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle Stove Top crumbs over soup mixture, then sprinkle seasoning packet over crumbs.
Pour broth over all; cover and bake 40 minutes at 350 degrees.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: pears with filberts(serves 4;  working time:  30 minutes)
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Spread the nuts in a single layer in a small cake pan or a roasting pan.
Toast the nuts in the oven for 10 minutes.
Test a nut for doneness by rubbing it in a clean kitchen towel; the skin should come off easily.
When the nuts are done, wrap them in the towel and rub off their skin.
Let the nuts cool to room temperature.
Put the nuts, brown sugar and butter into a food processor or a blender and process them just until the nuts are coarsely chopped.
Set the mixture aside.
Preheat the broiler.
Peel the pears, then halve them lengthwise and core them, rubbing them with the lemon half as you work to prevent discoloration.
Arrange the pear halves, cored side up, in a large, shallow baking dish.
Moisten the pears with the lemon juice and sprinkle the filbert mixture over them.
Broil the pears until the topping browns and bubbles, about two minutes.

title: marv's favorite chili
directions: Brown hamburger and 1/2 of onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Blanch broccoli in boiling water; drain.
Mix mushroom soup, mayo, cheese and onion with broccoli.
Crush Ritz crackers and saute with butter.
Sprinkle crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southwestern cheeseburgers
