directions: Mix beef, chopped onion and chilies. Shape mixture into 8 thin patties. Top centers of 4 patties with mushrooms. Top each with 2 slices cheese. Place remaining patties on top; pinch edges to seal securely. Place patties on rack in broiler pan. Set oven control to broil. Broil patties with tops 4 to 6 inches from heat 14 to 16 minutes, turning once, until beef is no longer pink in center and juice is clear. Serve on rolls with taco sauce and sliced onions.

title: delicious congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add lemon juice and cold water. When about half congealed, add pineapple, bananas, marshmallows and apples.
Chill until cold and add topping.
Combine flour, sugar, egg and pineapple juice.
Cook until thick and add butter. Cool completely.
Add Cool Whip.
This is very good.

title: mexican party dip
directions: In casserole dish, pour and spread sour cream. Make 2nd layer with salsa. Sprinkle Mexican cheese on top. Put jalapeno peppers on top (optional). Serve with nacho chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix sour cream and French onion dip together. Stir in taco mix. Then shred up lettuce and cover the top with it. Then dice up the tomato and cover the lettuce with it. Then cover the whole thing with the shredded cheese. Serve with nacho chips.

title: kaleidoscope salad
directions: Rinse and drain beans. Mix all ingredients. Chill in covered bowl.

title: peach dessert cake
directions: Cream margarine in a large bowl.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy (about 5 minutes).
Add egg, egg white and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.

title: cheese spread or dip
directions: Mix the 2 ingredients together and use on bread for sandwiches or use as dip for potato chips.

title: amanda's perfect peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll the dough.
Put peanut butter in the dough.
You put them in circles.
You put them in the oven.
You start baking them for 4 minutes on 1 degree.
You know they're ready if they are the color you put them in to be.
When you take them out, you put chocolate chip things in them.
Then you eat them.
You just eat them with your hands.

title: baked pork chops and dressing
directions: Season pork chops and brown in skillet; remove to baking dish. In skillet, add butter, onions and celery and saute.
Add bread and seasoning and stir constantly to brown or toast bread.
Remove stuffing to bowl; cool slightly and add water to moisten.
Place carrots and potatoes around chops.
Make dressing into balls and place one on each chop.
Combine soup and 1/2 cup of water and pour over everything.
Lay a piece of aluminum foil over top of baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes more.

title: hokey pokeys
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add cheese and stir until melted. Add Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Spoon onto deli miniature bread slices.
Toast under broiler for just a minute or two.
Serve warm.

title: crab meltaways
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, crabmeat, onions, salt and pepper.
Toast muffins.
Spread mixture onto muffins.
Broil until the cheese is bubbly.
Serve hot.
These may also be made ahead and frozen.
Let them stand at room temperature for 30 minutes before broiling.

title: easy red velvet cake and frosting
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, food coloring, shortening, milk, vinegar and cocoa in a large mixing bowl.
Blend together, then beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured layer pans.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done, at 350°.

title: terrific punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in large punch bowl and serve. Serves 25.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except paprika.
Place ingredients in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish and sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for an hour.

title: piccalilli
directions: Grind onions, peppers and tomatoes.
Sprinkle top with salt. Let rest overnight.
Drain in A.M.
Add sugar, vinegar and spice bag.
Cook slowly until all vegetables are done.
When done, put in hot jars and seal.
Makes approximately 14 quarts.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add corn, green beans, soup, sour cream and cheese. Mix well.
Mix together oleo and crackers.
Put 1/2 of cracker mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Add vegetable mixture and top with remaining cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve hot.

title: apple cider
directions: Mix together and simmer in crock-pot.
Serve hot.

title: corned beef spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Spread on party thin-sliced rye bread.
Place on cookie sheet and heat in 350° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: cream salad dressing
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and seasonings, then vinegar.
Cook in double boiler, stirring all the time, until about the thickness of rich cream.
Take from the fire and beat in cream.

title: vegetable-ritz casserole
directions: Cook vegetables to your liking.
Combine crackers with melted butter (should be crumbly).
Put vegetables in baking dish; cover with layer of cheese slices.
Top with cracker mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Thoroughly mix butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla extract.
Stir in dry ingredients.
(For a softer, rounder cookie, add 1/2 cup more flour.)
Add nuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Serve with a glass of good Wisconsin dairy milk to the "hurrahs" of everyone.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Blend ice cream, pudding mix and milk; allow to set 15 minutes.
Layer cubes of cake, pudding mix and jello mix.
Repeat. Top with Cool Whip.

title: peach pie
directions: Beat egg white until foamy; brush over the bottom and sides of pastry.
In a small bowl, combine flour and sugars; cut in margarine until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Sprinkle two-thirds into the bottom of the pastry; top with peaches. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot tuna buns
directions: Combine tuna, cheese, eggs, mayonnaise, relish, onion and salt.
Mix well.
Spoon into rolls which have been buttered and toasted.
Wrap each in foil.
Bake 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Place chicken in large Ziploc bag.
Add remaining ingredients to taste (enough to cover chicken).
Marinate for not less than 3 hours (24 hours would be better), turning sealed bag frequently. Cook on grill.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 200 degrees.
Combine oil, dressing and seasonings and mix well.
Pour over crackers and stir together well to be sure all crackers are covered.
Pour into a low pan (broiler pan or cookie sheet) and place in oven 20 minutes, stirring after about 10 minutes.
If you prefer your crackers with less seasoning, decrease crackers to 2 bags, oil to 1 cup, dill weed and garlic power to 1 tsp., salad dressing mix to one package, and lemon pepper to 1/2 teaspoon.

title: mary's fresh fruit salad
directions: Make sure that all fruit is completely ripe but not over ripe. Remove grapes from the stem and wash good; dry with paper towels; put into baggies and refrigerate.
Cut the honeydew melon and remove seeds.
Cut into 1 1/2 inch slices, remove rind making sure you get anything that is not tender and sweet; then cut into bite size pieces.
Put into baggies and refrigerate.
Do the same with the cantaloupe.
Squeeze lemon juice into water in a small bowl. Peel, core and cut apples into large bite size pieces, dip them into the lemon water as you work.
(This will keep them from turning brown.)
Dry on paper towels, put into baggies and refrigerate.
Do the same with the peaches or nectarines.
Cut watermelon and remove the heart of it, cutting into large bite size pieces.
Make sure that you do not get any seed in with what goes into the salad.
Put into baggie and refrigerate.
Wash and dry strawberries very carefully.
Make sure they are completely dry before putting into baggies with a paper towel in with them and refrigerating.
This can all be done a day ahead of time.

title: mom's overnight cookies
directions: Cream brown sugar, white sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and mix.
Stir in vanilla.
Sift together and add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Stir in nuts.
Form rolls; cover and refrigerate overnight.
Slice and bake in 400° oven for about 7 minutes.

title: fresh apple-nut bread
directions: Grease and flour two loaf pans.
Thoroughly stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
In the large bowl of electric mixer beat together at medium speed oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla until combined.
Gradually add flour mixture until smooth.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Turn into prepared pans.
Bake until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350°.

title: 1-2-3 cake
directions: Beat shortening until fluffy, then gradually beat in sugar. Next, beat in eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat into creamed mixture alternately a little at a time with milk.
Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out dry.
Bake at 350°.
Cool on rack for 10 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool completely, then frost.

title: sheath cake(delicious chocolate cake)
directions: Mix soda with buttermilk and set aside.
Sift flour and sugar together in large bowl.
Place into a saucepan the oleo, chocolate and water; bring to a boil and pour over flour and sugar, mixing well.
Add buttermilk-soda mixture and eggs.
Mix well and pour into a well-greased and floured 16 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until a straw inserted comes out clean.
Start cooking icing 5 minutes before cake is done.
Pour over cake while it is still warm.

title: pickled okra
directions: Trim okra without cutting pod; pack in sterile jars, placing 2 heads of dill, 1 or 2 pods of garlic and a small hot pepper on top.
Combine vinegar, water and salt and heat to boiling.
Pour over okra and seal while hot.
Wait one month before using.
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in large pan.
Stir into melted butter the Worcestershire, garlic, celery salt, Season-All and onion salt.
Mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour in oven.
Stir good every 10 minutes.

title: thick and chewy chocolate squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined flour and baking soda.
Mix well. Stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into well-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until a golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients until dissolved.
Bring to a rolling boil; cook for 1 minute.
Set off heat; add vanilla and beat until right consistency to spread.
If it becomes too thick for spreading, add small amount of milk, being careful not to add too much at a time.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and shortening. Add mashed pumpkin and fest of ingredients. Grease pan and pour mixture into loaf pan. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: bootleggers beans
directions: Put all ingredients in a large casserole.
Lay strips of raw bacon or cut into pieces on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat about 2 or 3 minutes and add 3/4 cup coconut.
Butter pie pan; pour in mix and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: garbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium skillet, brown beef, onion, bell pepper and garlic.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes on low heat.
In a small bowl, combine cream cheese and sour cream.

title: friendship soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown ground beef; drain. Add water, tomatoes and rest of ingredients. Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Add pasta; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes until pasta is tender.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in pan (13 x 9-inch). Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter.
Arrange peach slices over sugar mixture.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour batter evenly over fruit.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix by hand; let sit for 10 minutes.
Grease 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° uncovered for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes.
Add sugar, pumpkin, vanilla and lemon juice.
Sift dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan.
Add 1 cup of nuts on top of batter.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Flip out on towel that has been sprinkled with 10x sugar.
Roll up towel and all while still warm.

title: dressing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes a crisp dressing.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine onion and margarine or butter.
Cook, covered, on 100% power (High) for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until onion is tender, stirring once.
Stir in cornstarch and pepper.
Add milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook, uncovered, for 2 to 4 1/2 minutes or until slightly thickened and bubbly, stirring every minute or so.
(Mixture may appear curdled.)
Stir in all remaining ingredients, stirring every minute or so.
Serve with crackers, chips or vegetables.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix ingredients in quart jar.
Leave garlic in for 2 days, then remove.

title: sausage egg casserole
directions: Mix cheese, bread and flour.
Add cooked and drained sausage. Put in large casserole dish.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture over ingredients in casserole.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in a medium bowl with lemon juice, salt
and	pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla, sweetener and milk in bowl.
Dip bread until egg and milk are absorbed.
Place in nonstick coated skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Serve with syrup.

title: marshmallow rice krispie squares
directions: Cook butter and marshmallow cream over hot water until syrupy. Add vanilla and heat thoroughly.
Put Rice Krispies in greased large bowl and pour marshmallow mixture over the top, stirring briskly.
Press into greased shallow pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
I use a 9 x 13-inch pan!

title: coconut pineapple chess pie
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs, flour, meal, coconut, vanilla and pineapple; mix well. Pour into a deep dish pie crust. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat ball casserole
directions: Combine meat, oatmeal, milk, onion flakes, salt and pepper. Mix well; shape into 8 large meat balls and place in 2-quart casserole.
Combine catsup, vinegar, water and sugar; pour over meat balls.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings. Double recipe if you'd like and bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Saute pepper, onion, garlic and zucchini with sausage.
Put 1/2 of mixture in large casserole and add a layer of hot pepper cheese.
Repeat the 2 layers.
Top with sliced fresh mushrooms, if desired.
Cook 1 hour at 350° covered then cook 1/2 hour uncovered or until juice cooks out.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 can soup, beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasonings.
Press firmly in 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, spoon off fat.
Frost with potatoes.
Top with remaining soup and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes or until cheese is slightly browned.

title: nachos
directions: Spread 20 chips with bean dip and cheese on top.
Cook on High in microwave 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, eggs, milk, vanilla and salt.
Heat until thick.
Gently stir in banana slices.
Pour in bowl and top with vanilla wafers.

title: bachelor's roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place roast in roasting pan or Dutch oven; pour catsup over it, then the cola.
Cover pan, cook in oven for 3 to 4 hours; depending on size of roast.

title: salsa rancher
directions: Mix all ingredients using 1 tablespoon of lime at a time to taste.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: cherry-almond balls
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, vanilla and salt until light and fluffy.
Add flour and almonds; mix well.
Use a teaspoon of dough to roll around each candied cherry, shaping into balls.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly. Roll in additional confectioners sugar.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until well blended.
Add egg. Beat well and add flour, baking powder and milk.
Chill.
Roll 1/8-inch thick for a crisp cookie; not so thin for a soft cookie. Cut in shapes.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown around edges.
You can sprinkle sugar on cookies before baking or they can be iced with a powdered sugar icing using different colors.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add other ingredients.
Dump in oatmeal.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: favorite crabmeat casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook butter, flour, milk and egg until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Fold mixture gently into one pound crabmeat.
Bake in a greased baking dish at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: crispy peanut butter cookies
directions: Crush cereal to measure 3/4 cup; set aside.
Stir together the flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat sugar, margarine and peanut butter until smooth and creamy. Add egg; beat well.
Stir in crushed cornflakes and flour mixture. Drop by level measuring tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets. Flatten with fork in crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately from baking sheets; cool.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix well and chill before serving.

title: candy apple cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream butter; gradually add brown sugar and beat until light.
Add salt and vanilla and beat until thoroughly blended.
Gradually add flour, stirring by hand until well-mixed.
Divide dough into 32 pieces; roll each piece between palms to form a ball.
Place pieces about 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Chill 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°. Bake cookies 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from oven; while cookies are still hot, insert a toothpick in the top of each.
Cool on wire racks.
In top of double boiler over simmering water, combine caramels and evaporated milk.
Cook, stirring until mixture is smooth.
Place walnuts in a shallow bowl.
Dip cooled cookies into warm caramel, letting excess drip off.
Roll cookies in walnuts and set in miniature muffin papers. Makes 32 servings.

title: giblet gravy
directions: Brown margarine, flour, salt and pepper together.
Chop eggs and giblets.
Add all ingredients and cook over low heat until mixture thickens.

title: delicious oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in Dutch oven. Place in oven at 250° for 5 hours.

title: cabbage, sausage and soup
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add coleslaw mix, onion, celery and caraway seed.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated and flavors are blended, stirring occasionally.

title: almond cheddar appetizers
directions: Combine mayonnaise and worcestershire sauce. Stir in cheese, onion, almonds and bacon. Spread bread with cheese mixture and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 8-10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in pan.
Mix all ingredients, except pineapple, green pepper and tomatoes.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, about 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover.
Add pineapple, green pepper and tomatoes.
Cook an additional 1/2 hour.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese-rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in covered casserole at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Fry and drain sausage.
Spray a 2 to 3-quart baking dish with cooking oil.
Place half of cheese in bottom of dish.
Mix spices with sour cream and mix with the sausage.
Spread over grated cheese.
Beat eggs and pour over sausage mix.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: micro tuna round loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour mixture into baking ring. Microwave on High until done, about 2 to 4 minutes.
Serve plain or with cheese sauce.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix refried beans and taco seasoning mix.
Spread in bottom of dish (9 x 2 x 13).
Layer sour cream, then taco sauce.
Add grated cheese on top.
Heat in medium oven until bubbly.

title: quick fruit turnovers
directions: Separate each crescent roll into a triangle.
Spread 1/4 cream cheese on each triangle and leave a 1/4-inch border.
Spread 1/4 preserves over cheese.
Place another triangle on top and seal the edges.
Repeat with remaining ingredients and brush tops with beaten egg white and bake according to package directions. Sprinkle with powdered sugar to suit your taste and serve warm.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple but save syrup.
In a skillet brown chicken parts in shortening; pour off fat.

title: seasonal potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and dice potatoes into a pot.
Cover potatoes with water.
Boil until tender.
Remove from heat; drain off water. Add milk, butter and salt.
Blend until all lumps are gone.
Add food coloring to your pleasure.

title: stewed chicken
directions: Cook onion, garlic and celery in butter and oil.
Add tomato paste.
Add all the other ingredients.
If needed, add a small amount of water.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine salmon, eggs, bread crumbs, cottage cheese and onion. Shape into 12 patties, dip patties in crumbs and fry in butter until golden brown on both sides.
Makes 6 servings.

title: taffy apple miniatures
directions: Heat sauce over low heat.
Core 2 or 3 apples; cut in quarters and in half crosswise.
On long forks, dip in sauce and then nuts.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Remove skin from chicken; cut up into equal portions for cooking uniformly (breast can be cut into 4 pieces).
Brown chicken in oil and garlic.
Combine rest of ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and let simmer for approximately 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serve with spaghetti with oil and garlic sprinkled with Romano cheese.

title: green bean soup for 2
directions: Chop potatoes and onion into a saucepan.
Add beans and meat. Cover all with water and cook slowly, until all juice is gone. Season with salt, pepper and bouillon, if desired.
Add milk and let soup get hot, but do not boil.
Very good!

title: pork chow mein
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir until well blended and set aside.

title: lo-fat apple crumble
directions: Prepare crumble topping.
In small bowl with fork, stir together granola, salad oil, 1/4 cup packed brown sugar and 1/4 cup flour until blended; set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Peel and core apples; cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Coarsely chop raisins or leave whole.
In large bowl, toss apples, raisins, cider, lemon juice, 1/3 cup packed brown sugar and 1/4 cup flour until apple slices are evenly coated.
Spoon apple mixture into shallow 3-quart baking dish; sprinkle granola mixture over apples.
Cover with foil and bake 40 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 20 minutes longer or until apples are tender and topping is browned.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm with light whipped cream.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients, then nut meats.
Drop from a teaspoon, about 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: speed bake coffee cake
directions: In morning cream together the butter, sugar and salt.
Add beaten egg and lemon.
Sift and measure 3 cups flour into mixing bowl.
Blend Yeast Ferment with flour, then add sugar mixture. Knead into a smooth soft dough.
Let rise until doubled.
Roll or pat until 1/2 inch thick.
Place in shallow buttered pan.
Brush top with melted butter.
Let rise until doubled.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake about 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: no-fat-added-oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Rinse chicken; blot dry with paper towel. Coat nonstick baking sheet with vegetable cooking spray.
In shallow dish, combine cheese, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Into another shallow dish, pour buttermilk.
Dip chicken into buttermilk until coated, then roll in crumb mixture to coat. Arrange chicken on baking sheet.
Bake until crisp and golden brown, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: economy chocolate cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together into a large bowl.
Make a hole in the middle and pour in oil, vinegar, vanilla and water. Beat until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm milk.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Add flour and beat well.
Let rise to almost double in bulk.
Punch down and roll out on lightly floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in about 2-inch pieces (round, diamond or square).
Dip each piece in melted butter.
Arrange in buttered pans 1/2 full.
Let rise again to double.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fresh banana punch
directions: Mash bananas in blender with a little pineapple juice. Mix bananas, pineapple juice, orange juice and lemon juice. In a separate container, mix sugar and water; boil 15 minutes. Let cool; add fruit mixture and freeze as long as 1 to 2 weeks ahead. Take out 2 hours before serving and thaw to a mush. Add chilled ginger ale at serving time. Serves 50.

title: olive cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, Blue cheese and butter, then stir in chives and olives.
Chill slightly.
Form into a ball.
Chill well.
Press walnuts over outside of ball.
Serve surrounded with assorted crackers.
Makes 3 cups.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, 2 eggs, oleo and water.
Batter will be stiff.
Put in oblong (9 x 13-inch) greased pan.
Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar (save about 1/2 cup for topping) and the 3 eggs until thoroughly mixed.
Pour over cake mixture.
Add nuts on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup powdered sugar when cooled.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Boil cauliflower in salt water for 4 minutes.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add cooked cauliflower.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Toss lightly and saute until light golden brown. Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet dough
directions: Stir milk, sugar, oil, salt, eggs and dissolved yeast in large bowl.
Add 2 cups flour and beat well.
Add enough more flour to make soft dough.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes.
Add enough more flour to make soft, but not sticky, dough.
Let rise an hour or so.

title: penne with artichokes
directions: Cook penne al dente.
Simmer artichokes and tomatoes in saucepan 1 minute.
Stir in artichoke liquid and basil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Puree.

title: italian pasta sauce
directions: 1. Saute onion and add garlic. Make sure garlic doesn't burn; it burns easily.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, 2 cups flour and powdered sugar.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sift granulated sugar, 4 tablespoons flour and baking powder.
Add eggs and lemon juice.
Spread over crust.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost with powdered sugar frosting using lemon juice instead of water.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Chop onion and brown in oil.
Add to onion the catsup, sugar, water, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
This makes enough for 2 pounds of chopped ham.
Heat thoroughly after adding meat.
Serve on fresh buns.

title: scalloped squash
directions: Slice squash and add enough water to cook, when tender, drain and mash.
While hot, add grated cheese and margarine, mix well. Add evaporated milk, salt, pepper, sugar and eggs.
Add cracker crumbs.
Pour into baking dish and cook 350 for 45 minutes.

title: cheese balls(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Chop chutney very fine.
Mix with butter and curry powder. Add cheese and blend thoroughly.
Form into balls and roll in fresh coconut.

title: nutty bars
directions: Line a big cookie pan with foil. Arrange graham crackers on foil.
Mix margarine, butter and sugar; boil 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir well.
Sprinkle on nuts; coconut, if desired.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Let cool, then peel off.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Add potato chips. Make small balls and press out on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 12 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while warm but not hot.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Combine marshmallow cream, sugar, milk, butter and salt in
a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue
to boil over moderate heat, stirring constantly,
for
minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate and
vanilla.
Beat
until
smooth.
Spread
into a greased pan. Melt cream cheese; pour over and mix into fudge. Chill in refrigerator until firm.

title: lemon-strawberry punch
directions: Puree strawberries in blender (about 1 minute on low setting). Add lemonade concentrate and sugar.
Cover and mix on low speed. Let stand 30 minutes.
At serving time, add water and ginger ale and pour over ice in punch bowl.
Yields 32 servings.

title: potato puffs
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs. Add potatoes.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt. Stir into
potato mixture. In a large saucepan or kettle, heat about 1-inch oil. Drop mixture by heaping teaspoonfuls, 4 or 5 at a time, in hot oil.
Fry 2 to 3 minutes, turning once, until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields about 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding, powdered sugar and milk together with electric mixer, about 2 minutes, on low speed.
Fold Cool Whip into pudding mixture; set aside.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Fry cut up chicken until brown.
Mix all other ingredients. Put chicken in casserole.
Put rice mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: chocolate peanut butter pizza
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and mix.
Pat on a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Return to oven for 4 to 6 minutes until lightly browned.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Slowly heat Karo syrup and sugar.
Cook, stirring often, until sugar is dissolved.
Heat just to boiling.
Remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter until smooth.
Add cereal; stir until covered well.
Remove from pan and let cool slightly.
Form into balls.

title: pumpkin cheese-swirled pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In small bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Blend in 1/4 cup corn syrup and vanilla; set aside. In medium bowl, beat remaining 1/4 cup corn syrup, pumpkin and next 5 ingredients until smooth. Pour into pie crust. Drop tablespoonfuls of cream cheese mixture onto pumpkin filling. With knife, swirl mixture to marbleize. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between edge and center comes out clean. Cool on a wire rack.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: In a baking dish (9 x 13-inch), layer chicken and broccoli. Mix together soups, milk and pepper; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over top of soup mixture.
Bake at 350° (uncovered) for about 45 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together corn, salt, sugar and flour.
Beat eggs well and add milk.
Stir egg mixture into corn mixture.
Pour into casserole. Dot with butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown Beef and Onion; pour off grease.
Add Flour, Salt, Pepper and Mushrooms; cook 5 minutes over medium heat uncovered.
Add Soup and simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in Sour Cream and Noodles. Sprinkle with Parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick chicken and rice
directions: Mix together rice, soups and milk.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle chicken pieces with salt and pepper; place skin side up on top of rice.
Brush with melted butter. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top during last 1/2 hour of baking.

title: heavenly lime salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups of boiling water in a large mixing bowl.
Mash cream cheese in small bowl; add hot gelatin mixture and stir until dissolved.
Melt marshmallows in 1/4 cup boiling water in top of double boiler.
Add to gelatin mixture.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Add whipped cream; beat mixture until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour into greased mold, large baking dish or individual molds.
Yields 18 to 20 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage until crumbly. Drain.
Mix all ingredients and put in a 2-quart casserole. Cook at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine in blender or food processor.
Serve with vegetables, crackers or hollow out a round loaf of bread and serve with bread pieces.

title: mom's nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Place flour and next 3 ingredients in large bowl.
Drop in shortening.
Pour in milk, vanilla and 2 eggs.
Beat 300 strokes. Add 2 eggs; beat 300 strokes.
Beat until blended.
Batter is heavy.
Fold in nuts.
Bake.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: believe it or not cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° until light brown, about 10 minutes.
These are delicious.

title: oysterette snacks
directions: Pour oil over crackers and mix gently to coat.
Add dressing mix and garlic salt, stirring well.
Dressing will stick to crackers. Store in Tupperware containers.
Use as a snack or as croutons.

title: no crust quiche
directions: Crush croutons and mix with 1/4 cup melted butter.
Line bottom of greased 10-inch deep pie pan with croutons.
Mix rest of ingredients gently and pour over crouton base.
Sprinkle Parmesan on top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop by teaspoon or cookie dipper on cookie sheet.
Bake about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: tamale loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook onion, garlic, green pepper and celery in oil for 5 minutes.
Add ground meat and cook for 15 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add cream style corn.
Mix cornmeal with milk and stir into mixture.
Cook for 15 minutes longer, stirring constantly.
Add cream style corn.
Pour into greased pan, top with grated cheese and decorate with olives.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour.

title: morning fruit soup
directions: Cut fruit into bite size pieces.
Add fruit cocktail and water.
Put into large pan and cover mixture with tapioca. Simmer until tapioca is dissolved.
Serve over toast or waffles.

title: tahitian chicken salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl.
Add raisins, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a tube pan.

title: french onion soup
directions: Cook onions in butter until lightly browned, about 20 minutes. Add broth and Worcestershire sauce and bring to boiling.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour soup into bowls and place croutons on top.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: pizza bread
directions: Put bread on pan or plate.
Put tomato sauce on bread.
Put cheese on the sauce.
Put pepperoni slices on the cheese.
Put in oven for 1 hour, or until cheese is all melted.
Take it out, then cut with a pizza cutter.

title: cream potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes round.
Place potatoes in oil in skillet until brown.
Drain oil; add water to cover potatoes. Sprinkle flour over potatoes and add onion and parsley.
Stir every once in a while until thickened.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain liquid from asparagus.
Mix all ingredients, except enough cheese to sprinkle generously over top.
Pour into greased baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and bake in a 400° oven for approximately 35 minutes.

title: annette's little pies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Roll biscuits out, one at a time, and fill with apple and turn over like a fried pie.
Place in melted butter.
Pour 7-Up over pies and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake in oven until golden brown.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8-inch square baking pan with vegetable cooking spray and set aside.

title: cabbage and bacon soup
directions: In Dutch oven or kettle, fry bacon until lightly brown. Add onion and garlic and cook until bacon is brown and onion is tender. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until cabbage is tender, covered to prevent evaporation. Allow to rest 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with croutons or cornbread squares or muffins. Serves 4.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough. Knead lightly, about 1 minute. Roll out dough; cut biscuits.
Bake on lightly greased pan at 425° about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sour cream smothered chicken livers
directions: Pray.
Roll liver in flour and salt.
Cook over medium heat until evenly browned on all sides.
Add onions and stir constantly.
When well-browned, drain off excess oil.
Add lemon pepper, parsley and hot water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Add sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Serve immediately over bread points.
Makes 4 servings.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients (except for the nuts) and form a ball.
Roll the ball in the nuts until evenly coated.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with crackers or garlic toast.
The cheese ball is pretty when rolled in 1/2 c. fresh parsley mixed with the nuts.

title: broccoli pasta salad
directions: Saute garlic in chicken broth for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add broccoli and cook until crisp-tender.
Add mushrooms.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add tomatoes, green onion, hot pasta and Parmesan cheese; toss.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 2 servings.

title: potato soup
directions: Heat butter in a 3-quart saucepan and saute the onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add carrots, celery, potatoes, parsley, chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until the vegetables are tender, about 15 minutes.
Reduce heat, add pimiento and 3 1/2 cups milk.
Heat the soup until the milk is scalded only (it should not boil).
Blend flour with 1/2 cup milk and add it, stirring constantly, into the soup.
Cook until soup is bubbly and slightly thickened.
Enjoy.

title: cream cabbage(this was my mother, vera hancock dean's recipe.)
directions: Beat together in pan all ingredients except cabbage and cream. Stir over heat until boils.
Stir in milk; let boil.
Pour over chopped cabbage while hot.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Add meringue.
Sprinkle with coconut and brown in 350° oven.

title: seafood casserole
directions: In a skillet, heat olive oil.
Add garlic, onion and pepper. Saute until soft.

title: london broil with mushroom sauce
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; stir well.
Place steak on a rack in a broiler pan; brush with half of oil mixture.
Broil 6 inches from heat 5 minutes.
Turn; brush with remaining oil mixture. Broil an additional 4 to 6 minutes or to desired degree of doneness.
To serve, slice steak diagonally across grain into thin slices.
Serve with warm Mushroom Sauce.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: two-alarm pepper bread
directions: Place bread slices on an ungreased baking sheet.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Brush top side of each bread slice with margarine mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Serve warm.
Yields 4 servings (about 139 calories per serving).

title: basil-tomato tart(great for brunch or appetizer.)
directions: Unfold pie crust according to package directions.
Place in a 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish. Flute edges.
Prebake according to package directions.
Remove
from oven and sprinkle with 1/2 cup Mozzarella.
Cool on wire rack.
Cut tomatoes into wedges. Drain on paper towels. Arrange atop melted cheese in baked pie shell.

Process in food processor or coarsely chop the basil and garlic. Sprinkle over tomatoes. Combine remaining Mozzarella, mayonnaise, Parmesan and pepper. Spoon over basil mixture. Evenly coat top. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 375° until top is golden and bubbly. Serve warm. Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine egg and milk.
Soak bread in egg mixture.
Add other ingredients and shape into loaf in a shallow pan.

title: custard pie
directions: Place in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fast chile con queso
directions: Melt butter and cheese. Then add pico de gallo. Stir well.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake and remove bones and skin from salmon.
Blend in eggs. Stir in liquid from salmon plus milk to make 1 1/2 cups.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Spoon into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
If desired, the lemon juice may be omitted.

title: quick skillet pork and vegetables
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add pork; cook and stir 5 to 6 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove with slotted spoon; keep warm.
Add vegetables and 2 tablespoons reserved pineapple liquid.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Drain, if necessary.
Add pork, pineapple and sauce.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Serve with rice.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and banana. Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternating with buttermilk. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut roll
directions: Beat the eggs for 5 minutes at high speed.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
In a separate bowl, mix the remaining ingredients (except walnuts).
Fold into pumpkin mix and put in jelly roll pan.
Top with walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Lay out a cloth towel.
Sprinkle it with powdered sugar and after taking cake from oven, lay out on powdered sugar cloth and roll up.
Let cool.
When cool, gently unroll nut roll and spread flat cake with filling.

title: pineapple and orange salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix pineapple, oranges, coconut and marshmallows with sour cream until thoroughly mixed.

title: baked meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Roll in flour and place in a baking dish.
Cover meat balls with spaghetti sauce; cover baking dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: oh so good
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; pat down into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream oleo and brown and white sugars.
Blend in egg, soda, salt, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in flour and oatmeal. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Leave 5 minutes.
Spread chocolate evenly.
Drizzle with peanut butter mixture.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Have a large pot of water boiling.
Slice top from peppers, remove seeds and drop into boiling water.
Boil 5 minutes, remove and invert to drain and cool.
Mix the beef, pork, onion, potatoes, Angostura Bitters, cheese and milk together.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Place peppers in a shallow baking pan, add water until 1 inch deep. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve as is or with heated tomato sauce.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 19 g, protein 38 g, fat 38 g, calories 579.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine vinegar and sugar in small pan and bring to a boil. Cool; add salad oil and salt.
Drain beans, peas and pimentos. Combine with pepper, onion rings and celery.
Pour dressing over vegetables and stir well.
Cover bowl and let marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Drain before serving.

title: antipasto salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss cooked noodles with remaining ingredients until well blended.
Chill before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate delight
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and pecans; put in bottom of baking dish and bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Let cool.
Add second layer.

title: angel hash
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Mix in Jell-O, then cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Stir and refrigerate.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream the oleo and add all sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream, ending with dry ingredients.
Add flavoring.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Put layer of batter in bottom of pan.
Add half of cranberry sauce and spread around evenly.
Add remaining batter, putting remaining cranberry sauce on top.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake in a 350° oven for 55 minutes.
Remove from pan after 5 minutes cooling.

title: what is it?
directions: Blend flour, margarine and nuts together; pat into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
Layer on cooled crust. Follow directions on package and mix chocolate pudding, using milk.
Spread rest of container of Cool Whip and can sprinkle top with nuts or coconut.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: willie's sugar cookies
directions: Sprinkle
top of cookie with sugar before baking.
Bake at 375° to 400°.

title: no bake fudge cookies
directions: Bring sugars, butter and milk to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes. Place other ingredients in a large bowl and pour hot mixture over them.
Mix in.
Drop from a teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Yield:
8 dozen.

title: barbecued hamburger
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet.
Pour off fat that accumulates.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well, and simmer 20 to 30 minutes, uncovered.
Spoon onto hamburger buns.
Yield: 1 1/2 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:
200 (320 with bun).

title: chocolate (wacky) cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes in an ungreased loaf pan.

title: old fashioned cream of tomato soup(4b's restaurant)
directions: Mix tomatoes, chicken broth, margarine, sugar, onion and soda in saucepan.
Simmer one hour.
Heat cream in double boiler (or microwave) and add to hot tomato mixture.
Soup is now ready to serve and enjoy.

title: salted pecans
directions: Fill a quart jar with pecan halves.
Put 1/4 cup salt in jar. Fill with tap water.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Drain well.
Pat nuts on layers of paper towels, patting with dry towels until all water is absorbed. Place on dry towels and let stand in warm room two hours.
When thoroughly dry, toast in 225° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.

title: brown betty
directions: Combine butter and bread crumbs; toss until well blended, then set aside.
Prepare the apples, then toss with sugar, cinnamon, lemon rind and juice.
Layer the apples and crumbs in a buttered baking dish, beginning and ending with crumbs.
Cover the dish with foil.
Bake at 350° for half an hour; remove foil and continue baking another 10 minutes, or until the crumb topping is crisp and brown.
Serve hot, with cream.

title: oysters macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook on medium heat until cheese melts.
Do not boil.
Pour over ham/potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with 13 oz. can French onion rings.
Bake 10 minutes or until onion rings are golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: vanilla sugar cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add baking powder and flour, 1 cup at a time, mixing after each addition.
Dough will be stiff.
Do not chill.
Roll out dough on floured surface to 1/8-inch thick.
Dip cookie cutters in flour and cut dough into shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes until light brown.
Remove immediately from sheet.
Decorate with frosting.

title: herb bubble ring
directions: Let frozen dough thaw until pliable.
Cut thawed loaf into 20 pieces.
(If using roll dough, cut each roll in half.) Arrange in a lightly greased ring mold or tube pan.
Mix melted butter and herbs and brush over dough. Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown on all sides.
Remove from pan immediately.
Serve hot or wrap in foil for reheating later.
I usually thaw the amount of dough I think I'll need and then put in a large rectangular dish, depending on the number I need.

title: pineapple mojito
directions: Place ice and pineapple in a cocktail shaker and pour rum, lime juice and pineapple juice over. Add the sugar. Shake to combine. Chill. Pour the mixture into a tall, narrow glass and serve immediately.

title: chopstick tuna
directions: Combine soup and water; add 1/2 of noodles, tuna, celery, cashews, onion and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Place in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle remaining noodles on top.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Pass soy sauce.

title: nalisniki(lithuanian crepes)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Batter will be thin. Pour just enough batter into a
heated, buttered skillet to cover the bottom.
Turn when edges of crepe pull away from the pan and it bubbles up. After crepe is cooked on both sides, remove from skillet.

title: stove top rice pudding
directions: Cook milk, water and rice on top of stove for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Beat sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Pour into rice mixture and cook for 2 minutes.
Pour into serving bowl and sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Chill and serve.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook and mash carrots.
Mix with all the other ingredients and place in a buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Put first 9 ingredients in large pot and put on stove to simmer.
While pot is simmering, prepare the following:
Mix together ground beef and pork, eggs, bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Roll into small 1-inch meatballs; add to boiling pot on stove. Simmer 30 minutes, then add green beans and corn.
Simmer another 10 minutes.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar and soda.
In a saucepan, combine margarine, water and cocoa.
Bring just to a boil.
Add all at once to flour mixture; mix well.
Add sour cream and eggs.
Mix well and pour into a greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, no longer.

title: sausage grits casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain. Cook grits according to directions. Combine sausage, grits, cheese, eggs, salt and pepper. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with remaining cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars and eggs together.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Make cookies into little balls and flatten with a fork.
Bake 10 minutes in a moderate oven.

title: lefsenorwegian flat bread
directions: Cook and mash potatoes as you would to serve, with milk and butter.
Cool.
Mix with sufficient flour to roll out.
Roll about 1/4 c. of mixture thinly to about the size of pie crust.
Fry on dry grill.

title: four layer chocolate pie
directions: Bake at 400° for 20 minutes;
cool for 30 minutes.

title: spicy apple cake
directions: Peel, core and dice apples (3 cups).
In a small bowl, soak raisins in bourbon or juice for 30 minutes.
Heat oven to 400°. Grease and flour a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Spread 1 cup of pecans on a cookie sheet.
Bake 5 minutes or until fragrant and toasted.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 375°.
Chop pecans coarsely.

title: almond mushroom rice
directions: Saute almonds in butter until golden. Combine almonds with remaining ingredients.
Heat through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: dunes squash casserole
directions: Slice and cook squash until tender; drain.
Beat eggs well; combine with onion, green pepper, mayonnaise, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mix with squash.
Top with stuffing mix.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, or until hot and bubbly.

title: hot vanilla mocha
directions: Combine dry ingredients in medium saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk and water.
Cook and stir over low heat until hot.
Stir in vanilla flavoring.

title: tarragon and lime
directions: Combine ingredients and brush over two chickens, cut into pieces.
Marinate two to three hours.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add oil.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each additional one.
Add lemon juice, rind and salt.
Add milk and flour alternately, ending with flour.
Pour into greased tube pan with bottom lined with greased wax
paper. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Put in bottom of 9 x 13 pan and bake for 15 minutes at 325°. Meanwhile, cook in heavy saucepan: 6 slightly beaten egg yolks, 3/4 c. cream, 3 c. sugar, 4 Tbsp flour and 4 c. rhubarb, cut. Watch closely while cooking until rhubarb in tender. Pour into crust and top with meringue. Brown slightly.

title: egg rolls
directions: Use a wok.
Shred cabbage, chop onion, celery and carrots. Finely chop garlic.
Brown meat and set aside.
Brown garlic, onion, carrots and celery in 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes, then add meat and cabbage.
Cook until cabbage starts to wilt.
Remove from wok.
Drain in colander.
Let cool.
Roll mixture in wrappers.
Fry in hot skillet (water end corner of wrapper so it will stick).

title: grit casserole
directions: Cook grits until done.
Add eggs, milk, butter and cheese. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Put cucumber, onions (chunked), mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and cottage cheese in blender.
Blend until smooth; add pecans until chopped.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Put Jell-O in boiling water; mix until dissolved.
Add to blender mixture; mix until well mixed.
Put in 1 1/2-quart mold and chill until firm. Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 lightly greased 9-inch pie pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until set.

title: canned dried beef
directions: Melt butter in skillet and add dried beef and brown.
Add flour and blend until smooth.
Then slowly add milk, stirring constantly until sauce thickens.
Add eggs to dried beef.

title: stoecker's don't b-flat biscuits
directions: Sift together baking powder, flour and salt.
Cut in the shortening with fork until mixture resembles coarse corn meal. Add milk and blend until flour is moist and pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Knead about 30 seconds.
Roll 3/4-inch thick, cut and place on lightly greased pan.
Brush tops of biscuits with butter or margarine.
Bake at 475° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about a dozen.

title: thelma's sweet potato pie
directions: Mix and pour into a greased baking dish.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put hash browns in bottom of well-greased casserole dish. Mix all ingredients together, except butter and cornflakes.
Pour over hash browns.
Sprinkle top with corn flakes and butter. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: four bean casserole
directions: Cook onion and bacon together.
Add vinegar, brown sugar and mustard.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add all beans; mix and pour into a large casserole.
Bake for 2 hours at 325°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Heat sugar, mustard, salt, pepper, oil, vinegar, Worcestershire, dill and tomato soup until sugar dissolves.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp kabobs
directions: Clean mushrooms and marinate with the shrimp and dressing in a zip lock bag overnight.
Turn bag several times.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Boil shrimp in Old Bay seasoning for 3 to 5 minutes; drain. Let cool.
Peel and devein.
Melt butter at low heat.
Add garlic, lemon, onion and tomatoes.
Simmer until soft.
Add mushrooms. Add shrimp into butter mixture.
Cook and serve over rice.

title: italian barbecue chicken
directions: Combine dressing, soy sauce, dry mustard and minced onions. Pour over chicken.
Marinate if you have time.
Grill, bake or microwave, covered, until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until it comes to a bubbling boil.
Add
pecans
and
cook one minute.	Beat until thick, then drop on wax paper to set.

title: ambrosia in a cloud
directions: Combine fruit in a bowl and chill.
Fold 1/3 c. coconut into whipped topping.
Spoon about 1/3 c. of the topping mixture into each of 6 dessert glasses.
Using back of spoon, make depression in center and spread topping up sides of glasses, spoon fruit into topping lined glasses, sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Chill. Makes 6 servings.

title: crab and shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine and bread crumbs well. Melt margarine and pour over.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm with crackers!!!

title: cauliflower dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with cauliflower pieces.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed. Then add egg.
Beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Chop onion; cook in butter until tender.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: slush punch
directions: Heat pineapple juice, sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
In a blender or with a potato masher, blend frozen orange juice and lemonade and bananas.
Combine the 2 mixtures and freeze in a large bowl or decorative ice ring.
Thaw 1 to 1 1/2 hours (or less if you like).
Place in a large punch bowl and add 7-Up or ginger ale as you like.
Makes 24 to 30 servings.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Mix butter and milk together.
Add 2 c. flour to yeast mixture, then add butter and milk to mixture.
Let the mixture rise.

title: banana split
directions: Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: gen and kim's vanilla ice cream
directions: Note:
Recipe for full churn, 1/2 recipe for tabletop churn.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips. Pour over in large bowl the Cheerios and mix thoroughly.
Cool. Shake to separate pieces.
Add powdered sugar and shake to coat evenly.

title: pepperoni stuffed chicken
directions: Pound chicken to 1/2-inch thickness.
Place 1 slice of pepperoni and 1 slice of cheese on each breast.
Roll up jelly roll style and fasten with toothpick.
Dip each roll in egg, then bread crumbs.
Melt butter over medium-low heat.
Cook chicken 10 to 15 minutes, turning frequently.

title: super fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, salt, cinnamon and milk.
Add nuts and fruit.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: ti's spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer for 4 hours.
To can, put in pint jars and process 8 minutes at 5 pounds pressure or use hot water bath for 15 minutes. Makes 15 pints.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Beat egg with vanilla and butter.
Add to dry mixture.
Add baking soda to pineapple.
Stir into mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Mix all together.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candy cane rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add warm milk, sugar, shortening, salt, egg and 2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in cherries.
Add enough of the remaining flour to form a soft dough.
Turn onto a floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down; let rest for 10 minutes.
Divide in half.
Roll each half into a 12 x 7-inch rectangle.
Cut twelve 1-inch strips from each rectangle.
Twist each strip and place 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets, shaping one end like a cane.

title: heavenly sour cream cucumbers
directions: Combine all ingredients except cucumbers and mix well.
Slice cucumbers very thinly and add to sour cream mixture.
Marinate for 2 hours or longer before serving.

title: hamburger sausage
directions: First Day:
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl by hand until well mixed. Cover. Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Serve with vegetable strips, crackers or corn chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix bean dip, avocados, seasoning mix, sour cream and mayonnaise; spread on top of avocado.
Layer on a large platter in order listed.
Can add chopped chilies to bean dip.
Have plenty of tortilla chips for dipping.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in an 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan. Brown 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix the mayonnaise, sour cream, cream cheese and dry Ranch dressing; smooth over cool crust.
Top with chopped vegetables.
Press vegetables down.
Wrap in foil for 3 hours before serving.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Mix well.
Spread on cake and brown under broiler.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Crush sauce with fork; dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add gelatin to cranberry sauce and stir until smooth.
Place in refrigerator for approximately 1 hour until partially jellied.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate until set.

title: crazy dip
directions: Mix and chill.
I put mixture in a food processor for 5 seconds.

title: apple danish
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut in shortening.
Combine milk and egg yolk; add to flour mixture.
Roll out half the mixture on floured surface to fit an 11 x 16 x 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Place in pan and top with filling.

title: soy sauce marinade
directions: Combine ingredients.
Use to marinate beef, pork or chicken (about 2 pounds).
Seal in Ziploc bag and refrigerate for 6 hours.
The meat can be grilled or broiled.

title: tomato basil soup
directions: Cook first three ingredients over medium heat 5 to 8 minutes until hot, stirring often.
DO NOT BOIL or soup will curdle.
Stir in basil.
Garnish with grated cheese and parsley.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fruit and oat bran muffins
directions: In medium bowl, stir together all dry ingredients and spices. Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine buttermilk, egg whites and oil.
Add to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened.
Stir in fruit; mix and add raisins.
To bake, spray muffin cups with nonstick spray coating.
Spoon about 1/4 cup batter into each muffin cup.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins. These muffins freeze well.

title: chocolate and peanut butter swirls
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa together. Melt butter. Mix melted butter, milk and vanilla. Pour over sifted ingredients. Work until a firm ball forms. Roll out between 2 sheets of waxed paper. Remove top paper and spread with peanut butter. Roll up like a jelly roll and refrigerate. Chill well and then slice. This is best made in the winter.

title: glazed ginger carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender (about 15 minutes). Drain.
Add butter, syrup or brown sugar, ginger, orange peel and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring often, until hot.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Peel carrots; slice from top to bottom uniformly.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Put grated cheese on top.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Test with fork for tenderness.
Sprinkle Stove Top dressing on top before baking.

title: best chocolate frosting
directions: In a small saucepan, mix cocoa and sugar well; then add milk. Bring to a boil and cook 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Let stand 15 minutes; then beat 9 minutes or until creamy.
Let stand for 15 minutes, or until desired thickness.
Then spread on cake.

title: cheesy baked chicken
directions: Pound out each chicken breast with meat mallet as flat as possible.
On top of each chicken breast place 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Start at the small end and roll tightly, put 2 toothpicks through to hold.
Dip each breast in egg, then in crouton crumbs.
Sprinkle each roll with Parmesan cheese, or add cheese to crouton crumbs.
Melt 1/2 of butter in bottom of baking dish.
Lay rolls in dish.
Melt rest of butter and pour over chicken rolls.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, then turn breasts over and bake for another 1/2 hour or until browned.

title: mother's salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and flour in top of double boiler. Add vinegar (weak).
When nearly cooked, add margarine.
Cook until consistency of heavy cream.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight.

title: baked apples
directions: Core and remove all peel from apples except for a broad ring around the base. Place raisins and sherry in a glass measuring cup and microcook 1 minute.
Drain raisins, divide raisins and seasonings among apples, filling core.
Microwave on High for 9 to 10 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flour, soda and salt, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Pour into pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven until pick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place pie crust in pie plate. Mix all other ingredients in a bowl. Pour ingredients in pie crust. Place the second crust on top. Fold top crust under bottom crust to seal. Crimp sides and cut slits in top crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until crust is brown. Cool 10 minutes and serve.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift
dry ingredients together.
Add all other ingredients. Mix well.
Bake
in greased and floured pan 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Makes 1 loaf.

title: spicy chicken(microwave)
directions: Place chicken in oblong dish (larger pieces to outside).
In a 1-quart bowl, combine all remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling (3 to 4 minutes); stir until smooth.
Pour sauce over chicken. Cover with Saran Wrap and marinate 2 to 3 hours or overnight. Cover with wax paper and cook 25 minutes.
Rearrange and baste chicken after 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: apple butter
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Bring apples to boil in water, reduce heat and cook 25 minutes or until tender.
Mash.
Stir in all other ingredients.
Bring to boil and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Put mixture in jars to 1/4 inch from top and seal jars.
Leave in boiling bath water for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 pints.

title: beer drunk wieners
directions: Mix in a bowl and add two packages of wieners sliced up in bite-size pieces.
Marinate in refrigerator for 1 or 2 days.
Cook on low for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or in microwave until cheese melts.
Great for potlucks, main dish with a salad or side dish.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak apricots in water to cover for 30 minutes.
Drain and chop.
Cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs and add alternately to butter mixture with orange juice.
Add dry ingredients.
Add apricots, orange rind and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, lined with greased foil, brown or wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
This bread is delicious toasted, buttered and served with coffee.
Freezes well!

title: sweet potatoes and apricots
directions: Cut potatoes lengthwise; place in 10 x 6
x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle lightly with a little salt.
Drain apricots, reserving syrup.
Add water if necessary to equal 1 cup liquid and set aside.
Arrange apricots over sweet potatoes.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt and cinnamon.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to boiling.
Stir in sherry and orange peel. Pour mixture over potatoes and fruit.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven, basting occasionally, for 20 minutes or until well glazed. Serves 4.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg white until soft peaks form.
Slowly mix in brown sugar, then vanilla.
Mix until very stiff.
Fold in pecans.
With a spoon, place 1 pecan, coated in mixture, at a time on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool. Can be frozen.

title: apple-raisin strudel
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine apples and apple juice in a saucepan over medium-high heat; simmer for 3 minutes.
In a small bowl, stir together arrowroot or cornstarch, sweetener, cinnamon and cardamom.
Add to apple mixture; simmer for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add raisins and sugar.
Lightly spray each sheet of phyllo with butter flavored cooking spray. Stack sheets on top of one another.
Spoon filling along one of the short edges of the stack.
Fold in the 2 longer edges to create sides that will prevent liquid from running out as you roll.
Starting with the short edge where filling is spread, roll into a log and place, seam side down, on nonstick baking sheet. Spray roll lightly with cooking spray.
Bake for 30 minutes; let cool before slicing.
Serves 8.

title: beef pocket pies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Remove frozen crusts from pie tin (gently fold the edge of the pie tin away from the crust until the crust releases).
Place frozen pie crusts upright in an ungreased baking sheet; let thaw.

title: pumpkin dream bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat butter and 1/3 cup sugar until fluffy.
Add combined oats and flour; mix well.
Spread evenly onto bottom of prepared pan.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool slightly.

title: vincent price cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease 8-inch spring-form pan with butter.
Lay spring-form on side; put in few graham cracker crumbs.
Work around all sides.,
Lightly coat bottom.
Put in freezer for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put beans in bottom of a 6 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt; mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over beans. Slice cheese and place over top.
Cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 375° until hot, about 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: pasta and scallops
directions: Add enough olive oil to coat bottom of a nonstick skillet. Saute garlic until lightly browned (meanwhile cook pasta).
Add wine, scallops, parsley, oregano and basil to the browned garlic. Do not overcook the scallops. They turn white when they're done (approximately 10 minutes).
Stir frequently to saute scallops evenly.
Return cooked, drained and rinsed pasta to the pan it was cooked in.
Add scallop mixture to the pasta and mix well.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in 2 gallons of water to which the 2 cups of lime has been added.
Soak for 24 hours.
Remove from lime water and rinse carefully.
Soak in clear cold water for 3 hours.
Drain and add the remaining ingredients.
Let this mixture soak overnight.
Next morning bring to a boil and simmer for about 1 hour or until pickles become green and taste done.
Seal in jars.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Put first four ingredients in casserole and microwave about 10 minutes until tender but not mushy.
Add rest of the ingredients and microwave another 10 - 15 minutes.
More croutons can be added on top if desired.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve the lemon Jell-O in the 1 1/2 cups boiling water, then add the package of Indian Trail relish, celery, sugar and pecans. Let jell.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in an ungreased baking dish. Bake at 325° to 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden and bubbly. Serve with vegetables, crackers or corn chips.

title: finger toast(snackers)
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and cinnamon and nutmeg to taste. Spread on bread.
Cut into 4 strips each piece.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain all beans and put in casserole.
Mix ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, parsley, green pepper, mustard, onion salt, pepper and brown sugar (save some for on top).
Add mixture to beans.
Place 1/2 pound of 3-inch strips of bacon on top and the rest of brown sugar.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: velvet crumb cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches or layer pans, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
In large mixer bowl, blend all ingredients except Broiled Topping on low speed 1/2 minute, scraping side and bottom of bowl frequently.
Beat 4 minutes on medium speed.
Pour into pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly.
While warm, spread with Broiled Topping.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Stir cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple together.
Put in a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix on top. Sprinkle on pecans.
Melt butter and pour on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: orange date crescent claws
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl combine nuts, sugar and orange peel well.
Reserve 1/4 cup for topping.
Stir dates into remaining mixture.
Set aside.

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello and gelatin in hot water.
Add strawberries and rest of the fruit.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Let set and then spread the sour cream on set jello.
Pour remaining jello mixture on top and let set.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: broccoli quiche(weight watchers)
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Cut in margarine.
Add yogurt.
Mix thoroughly and form into ball.
Roll to 1/4-inch to fit into 9-inch pan.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let cool, then mix yeast, sugar nd water.
Add yeast mixture to milk and beat well, then add 2 cups flour.
Beat in 3 eggs, one at a time.
Now add final 3 1/2 cups flour.
Refrigerate overnight.
Spread dough out on cookie sheet and bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Mix together in bowl cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on top of cooled dough.
Top with your choice of freshly cut vegetables. Cut and serve.
It is also good with shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: broccoli and mushrooms in sour cream
directions: Place hot, cooked broccoli in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover. Set aside.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Blend vanilla wafers and graham crackers in blender.
In a large bowl, mix ingredients in order.
Put in a greased (with butter) tube pan.
Set in icebox (covered with foil) for one day and then turn out and keep covered in icebox until all is gone. Won't last long!
Very good!

title: dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; cut in shortening.
Add milk and mix quickly until it holds together. Drop by teaspoonfuls in 5 cups boiling broth or stock.
Cook 10 minutes, uncovered, and 10 minutes covered.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer the ingredients in a bowl in the following order: lettuce, onions, celery, peas, mayonnaise, cheese and bacon. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
This salad will keep 2 to 3 days in the refrigerator.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: May substitute your own favorite combination of vegetables.

title: coconut delight
directions: Mix and spread in bottom of 9 x 2 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: butter browned potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; cut each into 6 slices.
Dry.
Coat in butter in 2-quart baking dish.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake covered in single layer 20 minutes.
Uncover; baste and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's mexican mess
directions: In medium saucepan, heat tortillas in sauce.
Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole with tortillas and sauce.
Layer the ingredients as follows:
meat, 1/2 of the cheese, chilies, corn, soups and 1/2 of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cookies(polvorones)
directions: Cream the butter and sugar in a bowl.
Mix in flour, vanilla and pecans.
Shape dough into balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet and press lightly.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes.
Roll warm cookies in confectioners sugar.
Cool and roll again in confectioners sugar.

title: white christmas punch
directions: Combine sugar and water in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add evaporated milk and almond extract.
Let cool.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Peel and grate carrots fine.
Add remaining ingredients; blend.
Chill and serve.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Mix together and pour into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: dog liver biscuits
directions: Cut liver into small pieces; grind in food processor.
Put into mixing bowl.
Add cornmeal, flour and garlic powder; mix well.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Spread the liver mixture on the sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until done.
Let cool; break into small pieces and put in container in the refrigerator.
Your dog will love you forever for making this treat!

title: stove top meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in nonstick skillet.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes on medium heat or lower.
When cooked, cut and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender. Drain. In separate pan, cook carrots and onion in butter until tender. Stir in cubes, soup and sour cream. Mix with squash. Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: gooseberry pie(famous!)
directions: Blend together until smooth.
Add gooseberries and mix well. Pour into 8-inch pie shell and cover with pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°, then 30 minutes at 350° or until top is browned.

title: jello salad
directions: Bring Jell-O, water and sugar to a boil.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate.
When Jell-O is partly set, add crushed pineapple, apples and bananas.
Refrigerate again.
Cook pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg to boil. Cool well. Whip 1 box Dream Whip and stir into cooled mixture.
Spread on top of Jell-O that is set.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: orange cream salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Stir in Jell-O, then remaining ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: nacho platter
directions: If using, brown beef and drain.
Season with chili powder and cumin (if not using beef, season the refried beans with the chili powder and cumin).
Spread the beans in a shallow 10-inch greased dish.
