Sprinkle on the beef followed by the green chilies, Monterey Jack and Cheddar.
Pour taco sauce over cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Garnish immediately with layers of green onions, black olives, guacamole and sour cream.
Place dish on platter and surround with tortilla chips.
Serve warm.
Serves 8.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill and serve.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Dip chicken pieces in melted butter or margarine, then coat with crumb mixture.
Reserve remaining butter.
Place chicken in baking pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes.

title: campfire beans
directions: Brown the ground beef in a deep skillet or other heavy pan; drain. Mix in soup mix, add kidney beans and chili sauce. Fill chili sauce bottle with water and add to mixture. Mix well. Lower heat, cover pan and simmer 20-30 minutes to desired consistency; stirring often. Serve with French Rolls or French Bread.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Blend well.
Keep in refrigerator for 12 hours before serving. Makes 1 quart.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken-avocado tortilla soup
directions: In a 5 to 6-quart nonstick pan over medium heat, stir onion, garlic, cumin, oregano, chili powder and pepper until spices are fragrant, about 1 minute.
Add broth, tomatoes (including juice) and green chilies. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.

title: sandwich hot dish
directions: Mix sandwich spread together.
Make sandwiches.
Place in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix eggs and milk well.
Pour over sandwiches even with the top.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, add grated cheese and/or cream of mushroom soup.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Serve hot.

title: holiday punch
directions: Combine ingredients in large container or punch bowl.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Mix first five ingredients and put in a 9 x 13 greased dish. Top with corn flakes.
Pour margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cathedral window cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips and butter in pan.
Remove from heat and add beaten egg.
Mix well.
Fold in marshmallows and chopped nuts. Roll in 2 rolls on waxed paper in coconut.
Refrigerate several hours, then slice and store in tight container.

title: sharon's pralines
directions: Cream sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt. Cook over heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add butter and pecans. Continue cooking until candy thermometer reaches 234°. Remove from heat and beat until creamy. Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Mix all together thoroughly.
Put into the refrigerator for 18 to 24 hours.
Serve with egg biscuits.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
After letting it cool only slightly, poke holes almost to bottom as often as desired.
Pour pineapple with juice over warm cake.
Prepare pudding as directed.
Cool.
Pour over pineapple topped cake.
Chill in refrigerator.
When cold, spread with whipped topping and sprinkle with nuts or coconut.
Keep refrigerated until served.
Keeps for up to a week in the refrigerator.

title: tamales
directions: Meat Filling:
Place pork and beef in large pot and cover with water.
Simmer 45 minutes to an hour or until fork-tender.
Drain, reserving all the broth.
Break meat into shreds, fairly coarse, mixing it all together.
(I mean, the beef and the pork.)

title: cheese pecan ball
directions: Combine ingredients, form in a ball, wrap in waxed paper and chill until firm.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes.
Drain thoroughly and mix all ingredients together.
Top with crumbled crackers.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken for about 30 to 40 minutes on about medium heat. When chicken is almost done, start noodles. After chicken is done, cut into small pieces and put in a large casserole dish. In a boiler, combine all soups, 1 cup of broth from chicken, 1/2 cup fried onions and Velveeta cheese (you may want to cut up and melt in the microwave first). Continue to stir sauce so that it doesn't stick and burn. Cook on low heat.

title: easy, yummy cake mix
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix in salt, baking powder and flour.
Add vanilla.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Pour 4 cups water into large saucepan; bring to rapid boil. Drop frozen potatoes into water.
Remove from heat immediately; cover and let stand 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain potatoes at once. Spread onto paper toweling; sprinkle with salt.
Cool.
Blend together remaining ingredients, except eggs and paprika.
Add potatoes and toss.
Chill.
Garnish with eggs and paprika.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: braised leeks
directions: Melt butter in saute pan and saute leeks until coated with butter. Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, until leeks are tender (about 10 to 15 minutes). Remove bay leaf, cloves and sprigs of fresh thyme before serving.
Drain some liquid if leeks seem too watered down.
(Butter may be omitted from this recipe to make it no-fat.)

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix well the first 4 ingredients and boil until thickens.
Cool and pour over layered bananas and vanilla wafers.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain.
Mix cheese and margarine together.
Cover carrots with mixture.
Melt enough butter to hold bread crumbs together.
Place on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until browned.

title: cold noodles with spicy sauce
directions: In large saucepan, bring about 6 cups of water to a boil and simmer chicken about 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not overcook or meat will be dry.
Remove chicken breasts but leave water in pot.
Bring water to a boil again.
Do not add salt.
Add noodles and cook, stirring occasionally, until they are tender, 7 minutes or less. Drain in a colander and run under cold water until they are thoroughly chilled and the strands are separated.
Drain.
Sprinkle with teaspoon of sesame oil and toss to coat.
Set aside.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set overnight to chill.

title: snowy white icing
directions: Cream well the butter, shortening and sugar.
One at a time add the tablespoon of flour, milk and vanilla.
Beat 12 minutes with electric mixer.

title: stewart's strawberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and half container of whipped topping. Spread into bottom of pie crust. Place sliced strawberries on top of cream cheese mixture, then put glaze on top. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Chill. Garnish with whole strawberries or some crushed graham crackers.

title: dirt cake
directions: Break cookies into small pieces.
Layer 1/2 on bottom (remaining 1/2 will be topping).
Mix pudding and milk (set aside).
Mix butter, Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese together.
Combine mixtures; pour over Oreo cookies.
Top with remaining cookies.

title: meatball soup
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring ingredients in saucepan to boil and add meatballs.
Cook 20 minutes longer.
Add 1/2 cup milk, 2 teaspoons vinegar and 1 cup peas shortly before removing from heat. Delicious!
Yield:
4 servings.

title: dirt salad
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Put on top of pudding and milk mixture.
Spread layer of Cool Whip.
Put on top either a large bag of Oreo cookies or vanilla wafers, whichever you choose depending on pudding flavor.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Combine corn flakes and butter or margarine; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake 1 hour in preheated 350° oven.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown 1 pound ground beef and 1/3 cup onion in skillet; drain off excess fat. Add tomato soup, peas, salt and pepper to taste. Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; set aside. Make biscuits by sifting together flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl. Cut in shortening. Add milk and stir until dough clings together. Knead on lightly floured surface 12 times. Divide dough into 8 pieces. Mold dough around cheese. Place dough-cheese balls on top of meat mixture. Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on the package.
Mix with all ingredients.
Lasts 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: jean's carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except raisins, carrots and nuts.
Fold in carrots, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in lasagna pan.
When cool, ice with Cream Cheese Topping.

title: patsy's corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together well in large mixing bowl. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake in oven 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken divan(crescent squares)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Unroll dough into two long rectangles. Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press over bottom and 1/2 inch up sides to form crust.
Sprinkle cheese over crust; arrange broccoli over cheese.
In small bowl combine eggs, soup, salad dressing and mustard.
Stir in chicken and onions.
Pour over broccoli; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 26 to 31 minutes or until filling is set.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef, onion and garlic salt.
Cook 5 minutes.
Layer ground beef mixture, pinto beans, sauce and corn chips.
Repeat and top with cheese slices.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended well.
Shape into a ball and roll in pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve hot or cold.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in 2 eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with apple, lemon peel and nuts.
Batter is stiff. Bake in buttered and floured loaf pan in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes.

title: favorite brownies
directions: Mix all
ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or jelly roll pan at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: grape jelly meatballs
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onions, milk, egg, salt, parsley and pepper; roll into balls.
Cook in skillet and drain off grease.
When meatballs are browned, add chili sauce and grape jelly and simmer, covered, 25 minutes.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine all ingredients except steak.
Add steak.
Seal bag, squeezing out excess air; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Remove steak from marinade.
Grill or broil steak, turning once, until medium.
Heat marinade to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with steak.

title: dilly burgers
directions: Make ground beef into 12 thin patties.
Sprinkle on seasonings.
Place 1 onion slice and evenly divided dill slices on each patty.
Top with remaining patties and press edges together to seal.
Place in baking dish.
Combine soup and sauce.
Spoon over meat.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: dale's delectable brownies
directions: Melt and bring all ingredients to a boil.
Add, while hot, to a 1 pound box of confectioners sugar in a small bowl.
Add vanilla.
Mix well and spread on top of brownies while they and the icing are still hot.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Sprinkle on 1 pkg. instant pistachio pudding mix.
Stir until all roughly mixed.
Add 1 cup miniature marshmallows. Fold in 1/2 of a 9 oz. container Cool whip. Chill until ready to serve.

title: crab-swiss appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put 1 teaspoon mixture into each sheet. Sprinkle with paprika. Broil about 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: low calorie pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease or spray 9-inch pie pan with vegetable spray.
Place all ingredients in blender, food processor or mixing bowl.
Blend 1 minute, or beat 2 minutes with mixer. Pour in pie pan.
Bake for 50 minutes or until center is puffed up.
One serving (1/8 cut) equals 1 bread exchange, 1/2 medium fat exchange, 112 calories, 18 g carbohydrate and 6 g protein.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown rice in heavy iron skillet in butter until golden.
Just before rice is fully browned, add minced onion.
Mix rice with all other ingredients and bake in greased casserole, uncovered, for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: imitation mignon
directions: Mix ingredients, except bacon, and shape into 4 patties.
Wrap each patty with slice of bacon and secure with toothpicks.
Place on broiler rack 3 inches from unit.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes on each side.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Remove toothpicks before serving.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: homemade candy
directions: Mix cream, cocoa, sugar and salt in a skillet.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Reduce heat and stir constantly until mixture can be dropped into a cup of cold water and a ball forms.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla flavoring and peanut butter.
Place in a buttered pan and let cool.

title: pumpkin-orange cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oleo.
Add pumpkin, milk, orange juice and grated orange peel.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and spices.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with "Orange Butter Icing."

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel and grate potatoes and onion.
Let stand 10 minutes. Drain away liquid.
Stir in eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls onto hot well-greased skillet.
Brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 2-quart microwave dish.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Stir in nuts.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes on High until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla, cook 1 to 2 minutes on High. Add soda, stir gently until foamy.
Pour onto buttered cookie sheet. Cool; break in pieces.

title: chicken doritos
directions: Mix together Cheddar cheese, onion salt and soup.
Dice Velveeta cheese and place in bowl with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Heat until cheese melts.
In a large casserole, layer Doritos, chicken and Cheddar cheese mixture.
Pour Velveeta mixture over the top. Add 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower in 1 cup water.
Drain.
Combine cauliflower and next 4 ingredients.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 2-quart casserole.
Spread top with sour cream.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Cool
corn bread; crumble.
Also crumble toasted bread. Melt bouillon
cubes
in
cup of water.	Mix all ingredients. Add water or
broth to get desired consistency.
Bake at 375° until golden brown and firm.

title: raspberry buttermilk muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter. Add egg and buttermilk.
Mix just until dry ingredients are moist.
Fold in berries.
Fill greased or paper lined muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot pepper chicken
directions: Marinate chicken 6 to 8 hours in vinegar; roll in seasoning ingredients listed.
Baste while cooking with butter.
This can be done in the oven, but is much better slow cooked on the grill.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Meanwhile, in saucepan, melt butter over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Blend in flour, salt, mustard and pepper.
Return to heat.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly until sauce thickens slightly.
Add 1/2 cup cheese. Stir until cheese is melted.
Drain macaroni.
Combine cheese and macaroni in a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix well.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and paprika over top and remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.

title: mimi's messy s'ghetti
directions: In large saucepan, carefully brown turkey meat, separating into very small pieces as it browns.
Add onion flakes, garlic powder, tomato sauce, oregano and basil.
Stir together with water.
Cover; cook over medium heat for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon over cooked spaghetti noodles; sprinkle with Parmesan.
My grandchildren love it!
Spaghetti is really messy, but you will be adored by small children and ol' peepaws, too!

title: hot dog delight
directions: Cook hot dogs, onion and garlic in a large, deep skillet until onion is brown.
Reduce heat, then add the flour and let it brown. Now gradually add the water and the beef bouillon cube, stirring constantly.
Keep mixture smooth.
Add potatoes and parsley.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, salt, soda, sugar. Cut in lard and dry ingredients with a fork. In another bowl mix together dry yeast, very warm water and sugar and let rise. Add 1 cup buttermilk to flour mixture 1/4 cup at a time. Then alternate adding water mixture and yeast mixture. Pour onto floured bread board. Knead 8 minutes or until leathery. Store in refrigerator over night (will keep 4-5 days). Roll on very lightly floured surface 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick. Cut into biscuits. Bake 12-15 minutes at 425 degrees.

title: cheese filled french toast
directions: Blend cream cheese with filling until smooth.
Beat eggs; blend in milk and vanilla.
Spread filling mixture in a circle of 12 slices of bread.
Top each slice with another slice of bread. Tear edges off; press edges together to seal.
Dip bread in egg mixture.
Place dipped pieces on baking sheet; bake for 5 minutes at 400°.
Turn; continue to bake for 5 minutes.
Serve, dusted with powdered sugar.
Serves 12.

title: pineapple cheese ball(appetizers)
directions: Combine cream cheese, crushed pineapple, one cup of pecans, onion, green pepper and seasoned salt until mixed well.
Chill until firm.
Shape into ball.
Roll ball in remaining pecans. Garnish with parsley, sliced pineapple or cherries.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Reshape remaining ball for use again.
May be frozen.
Serves 15.

title: diabetic tuna casserole
directions: Beat the eggs and milk together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Bake in the microwave on Roast or Level 5 for 18 to 20 minutes or until the center is firm. Stir every 5 minutes while baking.

title: company chicken
directions: In bottom of pan, shred corned beef.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each piece of chicken.
Place on top of corned beef.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 3 hours.
Serve with rice or biscuits.

title: green peppers (stuffed)
directions: Mix ingredients (except tomato sauce) and put into parboiled peppers.
Pour tomato sauce over top and bake in a 13 x 9-inch dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and bake in loaf pan 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: crab meat and spinach casserole
directions: Thaw and drain crab meat.
Cook and drain spinach according to package directions.
In a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of croutons, spinach and crab meat, until all are used, beginning and ending with croutons.
Season white sauce with cayenne and pour over casserole contents.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° until heated through and bubbly, about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: twice cooked potatoes
directions: Dice potatoes and cook.
Fry bacon.
Mix all ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "easy" cherry dessert
directions: Add a little sugar and lemon juice to cherry pie filling.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle Jiffy cake mix on top of cherries, then top with chopped nuts.
Drizzle butter over the top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
May be topped with ice cream when serving.

title: trout amandine
directions: Cut fillets into 6 portions.
Combine flour, seasoned salt and paprika.
Roll portions in flour mixture and place in single layer, skin side down, in a well-greased baking dish.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons melted butter over fish.
Broil about 4 inches from source of heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
While fish is broiling, saute almonds in remaining butter until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and mix in lemon juice, hot pepper sauce and parsley. Pour over fish portions at once.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: limeade or lemonade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve over ice.
Garnish with mint sprigs and lime or lemon slices.
Makes 6 cups.

title: easy watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding well with milk.
Add other ingredients.
Stir by hand.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: batter for fried fish(captain d's)
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Dip fish and fry.

title: apple and cheese casserole
directions: Cream butter, sugar, flour and cheese.
Place apples in casserole.
Press cheese mixture over and into apples.
Pour half and half over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spunky meatball sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients over medium heat until mixture comes to a light boil. Turn down and let simmer for 5 to 10 minutes. This mixture will cover about 70 small meatballs. Cook meatballs and pour sauce over and mix until each meatball is covered with sauce. Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: pistachio inside-outside cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together; beat 2 minutes at medium speed. Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.
Split in 3 layers. In between layers and on top and sides put frosting.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: *To toast nuts, spread nuts on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° , stirring, for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned; Cool.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate in water.
Cool.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream the oleo and sugar.
Add eggs. Blend well.
Add melted chocolate.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Fold in pecans and coconut.
Pour in 2 round pans, greased and lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate loaf cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and blend well after each one.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour batter into a greased or floured loaf pan.
Bake in a 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Frost or eat plain.

title: sweet potato pineapple casserole
directions: Beat all together.
Butter baking dish.
Place 1/2 mixture in dish.
Dot with marshmallows and then add remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Dot with marshmallows and replace in oven for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: poppy seed ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Blend soft margarine, onion, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed.
Slice whole package of rolls.
Do not break apart. Spread mixture on both sides.
Place ham and cheese on top of filling.
Put rolls back together and wrap in tinfoil.
Heat 10 minutes or until cheese has melted at 400°.
Cut into size of roll or as desired.

title: all-purpose marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Best if marinates overnight.

title: bavarian beef sandwich
directions: Brown beef, onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Stir in gravy and cabbage.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes. Spoon 1/2 cup mixture on bottom half of each roll; top with cheese and cover with top half of roll.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage and onion together; drain.
Mix in skillet the butter, flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
After sauce has thickened, add milk and beaten egg.
Alternate cabbage sauce and cheese in casserole dish.
End with bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: fish house slaw
directions: Combine together. Dissolve well. Pour over cabbage mixture. Let set awhile before using. It will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken cordon conti
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pound chicken breasts lightly to flatten.
Combine flour, salt and pepper and lightly dust chicken.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large container and mix well. Store mix in an airtight container.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill for several hours or overnight.

title: eclair cake
directions: Put milk in a bowl.
Add pudding and mix as directed on box. Add Cool Whip and stir.
Layer bottom of a 10 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture on graham crackers. Put another layer of crackers and pour remaining pudding mixture on.
Add another layer of crackers and frost.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs lightly; blend in sugar, scalded milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in a 400° oven for 25 or 30 minutes, or until knife tests done.
Sprinkle with nutmeg to taste.

title: low calorie salad dressing
directions: Shake together and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths. Mix sugar and cinnamon. Shake biscuit pieces in sugar mixture to coat. Layer into a tube pan. Mix brown sugar, melted butter and nuts. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Pull chicken off the bone and cut into pieces. Place in bottom of a large dish and spray with Pam.
Cook onion and celery until done, then put over the chicken.
Cook the Stove Top stuffing.
Put over the celery and onion, then open cream of chicken soup with 1 can of water.
Pour over chicken dressing. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling hot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add Wesson oil.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately grated apples to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla.
Dredge nuts in some of the flour (if you want any in cake).
Bake in tube pan at 300° for about 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cabin weekend waffles
directions: I got health conscious and revised my family's waffle recipe to include more fiber and crunch.
Even my father approved.
I usually make these on lazy weekends for brunch.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add tomatoes, chiles, salt and pepper. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add cubed cheese.
When cheese begins to melt, add cream.
Amount of cream depends on desired consistency. Keep warm.
Serve with chips.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter and jelly in a bowl.
Stir in powdered milk and bran flakes or cornflakes.
Mix well.
Roll into small balls. Roll each ball in crushed flakes.
Makes about 25.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Drain fruit.
Reserve liquid.
Use 2/3 cup liquid.
Pour into mayonnaise.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mix boils.
Add stuffing.
Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add chicken.
Brush with additional mayo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Melt marmalade.
Arrange fruit around chicken.
Brush on marmalade. Bake for 15 minutes more.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook all meat well done.
Chop onions real small.
Mix all ingredients real well.
Cook slowly, stirring frequently as will burn.

title: chef fred's 3-bean salad
directions: Drain veggies.
Mix dressing and toss with veggies.
Chill 4 hours.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; reserve caps.
Chop stems.
In medium saucepan cook chopped stems and onion in 1 tablespoon butter until just tender.
Blend in flour, marjoram and pepper.
Add wine. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in ham and parsley. If using sausage, brown and drain sausage before adding.
Stuff mushroom caps with mixture.
Place mushrooms on 20 x 12-inch piece of foil and dot with remaining butter.
Fold foil to seal edges. Grill over medium coals.

title: salmon celery loaf
directions: Combine ingredients as listed and mix lightly.
Put into greased small loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven for 1 hour at 350°. Turn out on platter.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Mix all together except ginger ale in large bowl.
Makes 5 quarts.
Freeze.
Stir occasionally as freezing goes along.
Scoop out small amount and add some ginger ale.
Should be slushy consistency.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir in pineapple and strawberries.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Add
cornmeal gradually to boiling water and let stand a few minutes.
Add butter, salt and egg yolks;
dissolve baking soda in buttermilk
and add.
Fold in egg whites.	Turn into a buttered casserole.	Bake
in a 375° oven for 40 minutes.
May spoon out or cut to serve.
This is a very old recipe.

title: sweet potato crisp
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water 20 to 25 minutes or until tender. Peel and slice crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces. Place in a shallow, greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cut margarine into flour and brown sugar until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Add pepper, milk and pecans. Mix well and spread over potatoes. Broil 6-inches from heat until bubbly, about 6 minutes. Yield: 6 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash in thin slices and put with 1/2 cup of water in a 2-quart round microwave casserole dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook in microwave for approximately 15 minutes until tender.
Set aside.
Melt margarine and stir in stuffing in a separate bowl.
Grate carrot and onion in a food processor for smaller pieces.
Drain water from squash, then mix squash, carrot, onion, soup, pimento cheese, sour cream and 1/2 of stuffing together in a large bowl.
Spray casserole dish with Pam, then put mixture in bowl.
Pour 2nd half of stuffing on top.
Squeeze a small amount of squeeze margarine onto top.
Cover and cook for approximately 30 minutes in microwave.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put potatoes in a large mixer bowl and mash.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs, beating well. Add dissolved yeast and milk to potato mixture. Add enough flour to make stiff dough. Rise until double in bulk in refrigerator.
Make out into rolls and let rise again. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
These rolls freeze well.
Bake until slightly colored, cool and freeze.

title: purple lady
directions: Mix together. Place in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cocoa, milk and corn syrup.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until sugar dissolves. Continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until 234° or to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat; add butter and peanut butter.
Do not stir!
Cool to 110°; add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until fudge becomes creamy and loses its gloss.
Put into a buttered 8-inch pan.

title: butter pecan peach cobbler
directions: Pour pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with dry cake mix. Top with pats of margarine.
Sprinkle on pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: miracle pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Pour into a 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
All ingredients will separate.
Crust on bottom, cream in middle, coconut on top.

title: thick and zesty pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and set aside.
In a bowl, combine 1 cup flour, salt, oregano, onion powder and garlic powder.
Mix well. Add shortening.
Pour water/yeast mixture over all and mix by hand until somewhat smooth. Gradually stir in remaining flour (1 1/2 cups) to make a stiff dough.
Let rest 15 minutes.
With well-greased fingers, press into pizza pan, forming edge.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven and spread with pizza sauce and desired toppings. Bake for another 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown and crisp on edges.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Layer all ingredients in an oblong casserole dish.
Place in oven until bubbly, about 25 minutes at 350°.
Cheese should be on top.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add bananas, eggs, vanilla and buttermilk; set aside. Sift together the soda, salt and flour; stir in nuts.
Turn banana mixture into dry ingredients and stir briefly.
Fill well-greased muffin cups 3/4 full and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple pie a la mode
directions: Spread half of the pie filling over crust.
Top with half the ice cream; cover and freeze for 30 minutes.
Drizzle with half of the caramel topping; cover and freeze for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining pie filling; cover and freeze for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining ice cream; cover and freeze until firm.
May be frozen for up to 2 months.
Remove from freezer about 30 minutes before serving.
Warm remaining caramel topping; drizzle some on serving plates.
Top with a slice of pie; drizzle remaining caramel topping over pie and sprinkle with pecans.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger and add taco seasoning.
Put in crock-pot with beans, sauce, salsa and cheese.
Let cook until all is melted and mixed.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In skillet, cook zucchini, onion and garlic in margarine until tender.
Stir in parsley and seasonings. In large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetable mixture. Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased 11-inch quiche pan, 10-inch pie pan or 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mixture evenly into crust.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Cut into wedges.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In medium bowl, stir strawberries, eggs and oil.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and nuts.
Add strawberry mixture to dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: green and white salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower, celery and green onions in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring until well blended.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over vegetables.
Toss lightly to coat.
Cover and chill.

title: sweet dilled pickled okra
directions: Pack washed okra in 6 pint jars; divide garlic, celery seed, hot pepper and dill seed between the jars.
Combine salt, sugar, water and vinegar in large saucepan.
Bring to boil and pour into jars within 1/2-inch of top.
Seal jars and place in water bath for 5 minutes.

title: holiday nut cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix 3 cups flour, baking powder and salt.
Add this to creamed mixture.
In separate bowl, mix 1 cup flour with cherries, pineapple and nuts. Add to other mixture.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients and simmer 10 to 15 minutes. Good for chicken, ribs or anything.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients well, making stiff dough.
Roll out on floured board; cut out.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender; drain.
Layer casserole dish, starting with cabbage, then spread half of mushroom soup over cabbage, then a layer of ham.
Repeat.
Melt cheese in butter and pour over top.
Crumble crackers on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop the popcorn; salt to taste.
Place in roasting pan in 200° oven to keep warm.
Mix remaining ingredients, excluding vanilla. Cook over medium heat to "hard crack" on a candy thermometer.
Add vanilla.
Pour over warm popcorn and stir to coat.
Spread out on a buttered counter to cool.
After cooled, break up and store in Ziploc bags.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken, onion, celery, garlic and carrots.
Season with bouillon cubes, parsley, bay leaves and basil.
Remove cooked breasts and cut into small pieces.
In separate pot, cook wide egg noodles.
Strain and rinse in hot water.
Add to cooked soup.

title: tomato cheese melt
directions: On each bagel or muffin half, sprinkle half of the Cheddar cheese and cayenne pepper.
Top with a tomato slice.
Sprinkle half of the Parmesan cheese over each tomato.

title: strawberry pretzel dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and mix with pretzels.
Pat into a 9 x 12-inch baking pan and bake for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in skillet with small amount of margarine.
In skillet, brown ground beef.
Add onion and green pepper, salt, oregano and sauce.
Cook rice as directed on box. Layer rice, meat mixture and top with sliced cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Serve with rolls.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cup bars
directions: In a 3 quart casserole dish melt the margarine.
Add graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter, and powdered sugar.
Mix well and pat flat.
Melt one bag of milk chocolate chips and frost.
Put in the refrigerator.
When almost set, cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chinese egg drop soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to boil.
Add pea pods and bok choy; simmer until vegetables are cooked, about 4 minutes.
While broth is simmering, add beaten eggs, stirring constantly while adding the eggs.
(Egg mixture will cook quickly once it is added to hot broth.)
Serve.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients	(flour, baking powder, soda and salt). Cream
butter,
add
sugar
gradually and eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add bananas to creamed mixture, then dry ingredients. Mix
well	and
add
nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon cinnamon, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 cup finely chopped nuts.
Roll biscuits quarters in mixture.
Drop into buttered tube pan.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream
oil
and
sugar; add other ingredients.	Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, in greased and floured pan.

title: vegetable ribbon salad(from farm journal cookboodk circa 1959)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water, vinegar and salt. Divide into 3 parts.
Chill until slightly thickened; add cabbage to first part of gelatin mixture.
Turn into 6 loaf pans (4 x 9 x 2 1/2) to depth of 1-inch.
Chill until firm.
Add carrots to second part of thickened gelatin; pour over firm cabbage layers.
Chill until firm.
Add spinach and onions to remaining gelatin; pour over carrot layers.
Chill until firm.
Unmold, cut each loaf into 8 slices.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves. Makes 48 servings.

title: tapioca and fruit salad
directions: Open and drain all fruit, saving the juice.
Set aside.
It should be about 3 cups.
Add 1/2 cup orange juice.
Cook the pudding, using the 3 1/2 cups juice as you would milk.
Cool the pudding.
Drain the cherries and wash them often so the color won't mix with the fruit.
Slice the bananas over the drained fruit and cherries.
Pour the tapioca pudding over all.
Chill for at least 1 hour, or keep overnight in refrigerator.

title: spaghettini bolognese
directions: Saute mushrooms, carrot, garlic, onion, celery and green pepper in vegetable oil in Dutch oven.
Add sausage and cook until sausage loses redness.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Simmer over hot cooked spaghetti.

title: heath bars
directions: Foil line a cookie sheet with sides.
Line bottom with about 40 soda crackers.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar with oleo; bring to a boil.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over crackers and put in oven for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle 2 cups chocolate chips over top and put in oven at 375° for 1 minute.
Take out and spread evenly. Cool 2 hours and break into pieces.

title: laura's spinach quiche
directions: Make 1 pie at a time.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Put spinach, cheese and onion into pie shells.
Pour eggs, milk, salt and pepper over spinach mixture.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes; turn oven down to 350°.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
These do not freeze well.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Season deboned chicken breasts with garlic salt. Coat chicken in mixture of spicy mustard and sour cream. Cover chicken breasts with Italian bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes on cookie sheet.
(I lay mine on aluminum foil.)

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Dice and cook potatoes until tender. Drain.
In saucepan, combine sour cream, onions, soup and margarine.
Stir constantly over low heat until margarine melts.
Add 8 ounces of cheese to this mixture.
Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Pour the combined ingredients over potatoes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pink cloud
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and gelatin together.
Drain crushed pineapple and peaches.
Mash up peaches.
Mix with gelatin mixture.
Put in refrigerator overnight.

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil together.
Mix all other ingredients and then add egg mixture, chopped nuts and apple pie filling.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: wet pizza
directions: On a large pie plate, or similar size platter, layer items in order given.
Let sit in refrigerator several hours before serving.
Serve with chips or crackers that are good for dipping.

title: phil's own easy 8 bean soup(easy, quick and tastes like hours of preparation!)
directions: Trim fat from meat.
In large kettle, put meat, all beans, celery and onion.

Rinse cans with a little water; pour into one of the cans and add to soup along with 3 to 4 more cans of water. Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring from time to time.
When celery and onion are done, meat will be done.
Shred meat into soup if you wish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
At this point, you can serve as is or add chili sauce in pot or on side if you like it spicy as I do.

title: toll house kookie brittle
directions: Combine margarine, vanilla and salt in bowl.
Blend well. Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar.
Add flour, chocolate chips and nuts.
Press evenly into ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Break into irregular pieces.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes 1 3/4 pounds.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Make a well and add eggs, buttermilk and oil. Stir just to moisten. Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes. Batter may be kept for six weeks in refrigerator. Add raisins and nuts if desired.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together and roll in small balls. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: pink lady cake
directions: Bake as directed on cake mix box in a rectangular box.

title: mrs. goad's chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until very tender.
Remove skin and debone.
Mix together cream of chicken soup, peas and carrots, 2 cups chicken broth and chicken.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Place biscuits on top and bake in a 400° to 425° oven until biscuits are done.

title: oyster soup
directions: Heat oil and brown flour to make roux. Add finely chopped onion and onion tops. Cook until onions begin to melt. Add 1/2 of water; cover and cook 10 minutes or until onions are soft. Add oysters, parsley, salt and pepper; cook and add remaining water or more if you like lots of juice. Add spaghetti and cook 3 to 5 minutes. Serve.

title: streusel topped fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spoon pie filling into pastry shell. In bowl, combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in nuts.
Crumble over pie filling. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until top is golden and filling is bubbly.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes 8 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: First drain pineapple; set aside.
Then mix by hand the Cool Whip and powdered pudding.
Then add nuts and pineapple.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours, then serve.

title: eggless, milkless, butterless cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Boil together sugar, water, Crisco, raisins, nutmeg and cinnamon. Let cool, then add flour, soda, salt and powder (also nuts if you are using). Bake in square pan or bread pan 35 minutes.

title: melva's angel delight(salad or dessert)
directions: Note:
May add a few maraschino cherries for color.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water; stir just until blended. Bake at 400° in a 10-inch skillet or greased baking pan until lightly browned on top, about 30 minutes.

title: pea soup
directions: Bring water to boiling with ham hocks for 15 minutes.
Add peas, celery, onion and carrot.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Add garlic salt to taste.
Add water as needed.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with raisins, coconut, chopped nuts, fruit and Eagle Brand milk.
Line pan with wax paper or Reynolds Wrap.
Pack mixture into pan.
Press firmly.
Cover with foil; refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: basic black and gold(hors d'oeuvres)
directions: Mix well.
This can be served hot or cold as dip, spread or in balls.

title: hot cabbage slaw
directions: Cook about 15 minutes or until soft.
When soft, add sugar, vinegar, sour cream, butter and flour.
Bring to a boil.

title: quick and zesty soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat.
Cook until noodles are done.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until water evaporates.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener, oil, vanilla and spices.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix well and drop by tablespoon in hot oil.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients, except coconut.
Blend on low for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch deep dish pie dish. Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle on coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: harvard carrots
directions: Slice carrots and cook in salted water for 15 minutes.
Drain. Combine sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and water.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add sauce and margarine to carrots.
Heat until margarine melts.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: ham crescent rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix cream cheese and half the honey together in a bowl.
Spread over crescent triangles.

title: mystery salad
directions: Heat soup; stir in cream cheese until it melts.
Dissolve jello in boiling water and add to soup mixture.
Cool to room temperature.
Add salad dressing, chopped veggies and pecans.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into an oiled 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares and garnish each square with a parsley leaf.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 stick butter and 2 eggs together.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1 stick of butter, 2 eggs and powdered sugar together.
Spread on top of first layer. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and cocoa together, then add butter, eggs and oatmeal.
Stir well.
Add sifted flour and baking powder alternately with milk, starting with flour and ending with flour.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet (greased) two inches apart.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: supper sandwich bake
directions: Spread butter on bread; put in pan and toast.
Combine beef, catsup and salt and spread on toast.
Top with frankfurters, cut almost in half lengthwise.
Add onion slices and cheese slices. Combine eggs and milk; pour over the bread.
Bake in moderate oven for 50 minutes.
Makes 6 sandwiches.
This is a meal in itself.

title: old fashioned fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, milk, salt and corn syrup until forms a soft ball in a cup of cold water.
Add butter and vanilla; beat! beat! beat!
(The secret to this fudge is in beating it long enough!) Add pecans just before pouring.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Coat bread dough with butter; let rise per directions on the package. Roll out dough; layer pepperoni and cheese as thick as you like. Fold over and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Makes 1 loaf.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain. Add tomatoes, water, noodles and seasoning. Stir to moisten noodles. Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until noodles are tender. Stir in corn and mushrooms.
Heat thoroughly. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican special
directions: Brown ground beef with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Put 6 tortillas in bottom of pan.
Spread ground beef over this.
Add El Paso Mexi beans and spread sliced or grated cheese over the beans. Add other 6 tortillas.
Mix together chicken soup and the can of tomatoes and green chilies and spread over the tortillas.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: waldorf or red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of cocoa and red coloring.
Add to eggs and sugar mixture.
Add salt, buttermilk, flour and extract.
Add soda to batter (sprinkle over top of batter) and blend on low speed.
Sprinkle vinegar over top of batter and blend into it until well mixed.
Bake in two 9-inch cake pans after preparing the pans with Pam or shortening and flour on sides and bottom.
Bake at 350° until springs back when touched.
Frost with Red Velvet Cake Frosting.

title: bean bundles
directions: Arrange beans in bundles of 8, wrapping a half slice bacon around each bunch.
Place in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour dressing over beans.
Cover and chill 3 hours.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove from dish with slotted spoon. Garnish with pimento.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Blend together the sugar, flour and mustard.
Stir pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Drop sausage in sauce and simmer slowly for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine all ingredients except cheese, chips and almonds.
Place in large shallow casserole.
Top with cheese, chips and almonds.
May refrigerate overnight.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°.
Serves 6.

title: pistolettes
directions: Brown meat; add Tony's seasoning.
Cook broccoli; add cheese and broccoli to meat.
Cut end of pistolettes off; cut center out with knife.
Stuff with mixture.
Melt butter.
Add garlic powder. Roll each stuffed pistolette in butter.
Put in pan and bake until golden brown.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of muffin cups, or line with paper baking cups.

title: tropical punch
directions: Thaw concentrated juices and combine in a large container. Add water and sugar. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill well. Add ginger ale.
Pour punch into punch bowl with block of ice.
With toothpicks, fix cherries into center of pineapple slices.
Float pineapple, banana and lime on punch.
Yields about 30 punch cup servings.

title: chocolate chip cookie bars
directions: Beat egg; add oil, then remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and flour.
Blend in milk.
Add margarine and syrup.
Microwave on High for 3 to 6 minutes.
Stir in vanilla; mix well.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken rice pom-poms
directions: Cook until soft, but not brown, first 3 ingredients in 1 1/2 tablespoons of margarine.
Blend in 3 tablespoons flour, poultry seasoning and pepper; add, stirring until mixture thickens the milk and bouillon.
Cool.
Combine with cooled sauce in large bowl the rice, chicken and Cheddar cheese.
Combine in a shallow dish, dry bread crumbs.
Using 1/3 cup of chicken mixture for each, form into 8 balls and roll each ball into the bread crumbs.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Blend all together; warm in pot.
Serve warm.
Great with mixed vegetables (carrots, celery, cucumber, cauliflower, cherry tomatoes).

title: raisin sauce for baked ham
directions: Measure cornstarch into saucepan.
Gradually stir in apple cider.
Add butter and raisins.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until the sauce thickens.
Boil and stir one minute. Serve warm.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix 1/2 cup oil to cake mixture; add 4 eggs and stir, then add 1 cup water.
Stir, then gradually add the lemon pudding.
Pour in 2 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fried chicken strips
directions: Cut chicken in 1-inch wide strips. Season heavily with Creole seasoning.
Soak in egg and milk mixture a minimum of 1 hour or up to 12 hours.
The longer it soaks, the more tender it will be.
At least 15 minutes prior to deep frying, put chicken strips (that have been drained) in a bag with enough flour to coat well. Shake bag of chicken and flour until coated completely.
Let chicken stay in bag of flour until oil is hot. Drop strips in oil and fry. Do not overcook.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mrs. peavyhouse's cheese mold and dressing
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Set aside.
Using a fork, cream together cottage cheese, cream cheese, salt and sugar. Dissolve soaked gelatin over hot water and quickly add heavy cream, then quickly stir into cheeses.
Add nuts, onion, pepper and olives.
(Reserve some olives for garnish.)
Have 5 cup ring mold well oiled.
Arrange garnish in bottom.
Press in cheese firmly. Refrigerate.
Serve with dressing.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing.
Set aside.
Mix Velveeta, soups and Pet milk.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Layer in casserole dish beginning with stuffing, chicken, then liquid.
Repeat 2 or 3 times.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add 1 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with chocolate syrup, beginning and ending with flour. Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 28 minutes.
Cool.

title: asparagus rolls
directions: Use a rolling pin to flatten each slice of bread.
Combine whipped cream cheese, chives and bacon, stirring well.
Spread bread with cheese mixture, covering edges.
Place 2 asparagus spears on each slice of bread.
Roll up and place seam side down on a greased cookie baking sheet.
Melt butter and brush each roll with butter.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and crushed bacon. Cook at 350° until brown.
Fasten edges of bread good with cream cheese mixture.
You may wish to use toothpicks to hold bread closed.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together well.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.
A few drops of yellow food coloring may be added.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Microwave onions, celery and bell peppers in 2 tablespoons margarine for 2 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: earthworm pie
directions: To prepare earthworms:
Boil 3 times in clean water each time. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes to crisp, then crumble.

title: chicken wings
directions: Set rack in a 6-quart roaster oven (Nesco); cover.
Preheat to 425°.
Disjoint wings; discard wing tip ends.
Combine remaining ingredients except margarine; stir until well mixed.
Dip wings in melted margarine, then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place on rack.
Cover; roast 10 minutes.
Rearrange center wings to outside edge.
Cover; roast 10 to 15 minutes or until crispy and browned. Makes 16 pieces.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese and herbs
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add onions and garlic.
Cook until tender, without browning.
Reserve.
Heat milk, rosemary, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Reserve.
Combine cheese with bread crumbs.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Make crust according to directions on bag of graham cracker crumbs.
Add nuts to crust.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Mix together powdered sugar, Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread this over crust.
Mix pudding by directions on box and add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Spread this over the first layer.
Spread the rest of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle nuts (very fine) on top.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: In skillet, heat oil. In a sauce pan, mix green chili peppers, milk, soups, and water. Dip tortillas into hot oil just long enough to get them hot; dip tortilla in soup mixture. Remove tortillas and place a small amount of onions and cheese on each one. Roll up each tortilla and place in a baking dish. Pour rest of soup mixture over; add more onions and cheese. Cover with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350° or until onions are cooked and cheese is melted. If desired, you can brown ground meat and use inside tortilla and sprinkle on top.

title: chocolate peppermint log
directions: Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with aluminum foil; generously grease foil.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Set aside.

Beat egg yolks with vanilla on high speed about 3 minutes; gradually add 1/3 cup sugar, beating 2 additional minutes. Combine dry ingredients into egg yolk mixture, then fold chocolate mixture into egg whites, spread evenly in pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly touched. Immediately invert onto towel sprinkled with confectioners sugar. Carefully peel off aluminum foil.
Roll cake in towel starting from narrow end; place on wire rack to cool.
Prepare Peppermint Filling.
Unroll cake; remove towel and spread with filling, reroll cake.
Glaze with Chocolate Glaze; chill.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: gourmet garlic butter
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Spread over bread to make delicious garlic toast.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Blend these three ingredients together until well blended.
Toss together with broccoli mixture.
Better if refrigerated overnight.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar, salt and water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add dry yeast.
Stir in eggs.
Add flour.
Mix until dough is well blended.
Use now or cover and put in greased bowl. Refrigerate until needed.
Roll dough; cut and dip in butter.
Let rise until doubles in bulk.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until browned.

title: foil wrapped chuck roast
directions: Place roast on aluminum foil.
Pour soup and dry soup mix over meat.
Wrap tightly in foil and place in pan in 350° oven for approximately 2 hours.

title: sour cream salad dressing
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add cream.
Beat well.
Add eggs; cook slowly using eggbeater, not spoon.

title: primavera tomato sauce
directions: Brown garlic in the oil.
Add fresh tomatoes or 1 can.
Add parsley, basil, salt, pepper and sugar; add desired sliced vegetables.
Cook until just tender (do not overcook).
Serve with cooked spaghetti; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Good with garlic bread.

title: marinated ribs for grill
directions: Bring ribs to a boil in a large pan.
Simmer 1/2 hour. Marinate ribs 4 hours in refrigerator.
Grill 20 to 30 minutes.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put 1/2 gallon ice cubes on top. Let soak for 1 hour.

title: old-fashion pickles
directions: Do not soak or peel cucumbers.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Pour sugar over rhubarb and let set while making batter.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Shape into loaf. Place in baking dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
In saucepan, mix catsup, brown sugar and beef base.
Heat until brown sugar is mixed well.
Spread on top of baked meat loaf and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: brunch omelette with canadian bacon
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Cut Canadian bacon into 24 (18-inch) slices. Arrange on aluminum foil and cover with maple syrup. Set aside. Heat butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish until melted. Tilt the dish to coat the entire bottom. Beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt in a large bowl until blended. Stir in onions. Pour into dish. Bake omelette mixture as well as bacon about 35 minutes or until eggs are set but moist and bacon is hot. Transfer omelette to large platter with bacon. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly, adding carrots last.
Bake in three 8-inch cake pans for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix pumpkin, oil, water, eggs and sugar together.
In separate bowl, measure out flour, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add to pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour mixture into 4 medium size pans; spray pans with Pam or grease and flour first. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool in pans for 15 to 20 minutes. Remove from pans and let cool on racks before wrapping in foil.

title: chocolate mint meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease (or spray with cooking spray) 2 cookie sheets.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, and beat until soft peaks form.
Stir in food coloring and mint extract.
Gently fold in chocolate chips.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel and dice the eggplant and cook in a small amount of water until easily pierced with fork. Drain well and mash with potato masher until mushy.
Set aside. Brown the ground round and drain thoroughly. Set aside. Saute onion and celery in small amount of vegetable oil until onion is translucent.
Mix eggplant, ground round, rice and spices.
Put mixture in buttered casserole dish and cover with bread crumbs dotted with butter. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: grandma quenqua's cabbage soup
directions: Coarsely shred cabbage.
In 4-quart saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes until cabbage is tender.
Serve with hot crispy bread.

title: salmon vegetable bake
directions: Stir together the soup and milk.
Cook in microwave on High until boiling, stirring every 2 minutes.
Stir in uncooked rice. Cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Remove skin and bone from salmon and break into large chunks.
Add remaining ingredients to soup-rice mixture.
Mix until combined.
Cook on High, uncovered, 5 to 7 minutes until heated through, stirring after 3 minutes. Top with French fried onions.
Cook on High 1 minute.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Heat oven to 370°.
In saucepan, heat spaghetti sauce and water.
Combine Ricotta, 2 cups Mozzarella, Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Pour 3/4 cup of sauce in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange 3 pieces uncooked pasta lengthwise over sauce.
Pour 1/2 cup sauce over pasta; spread with half (1/2) cheese mixture. Cover with 1/2 cup sauce.
Repeat layers.
Top with pasta and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: fideo(mexican spaghetti)
directions: Mash or shred fideo and set aside.
Saute onion and set aside. Fry hamburger, drain and set aside.
Open tomatoes and set aside. Open chilies and set aside.
Open broth and set aside.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add to creamed mixture and blend thoroughly the flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda.
Blend in chips and nuts.
Drop onto a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cookies stand on the sheet for 1 to 2 minutes before removing to a cooling rack.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In greased casserole dish, layer dressing, cheese, peas and chicken. Mix soup and sour cream together. Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring water to a boil in 3-quart saucepan.
Add potatoes, celery, onion, green onion, salt and pepper. Reduce heat and simmer slowly 25 minutes. Stir in evaporated milk and bring to a boil. Just before serving, add the butter.
This reheats very well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mother's gingerbread
directions: Cream Crisco and butter; add sugar gradually while creaming. Sift dry ingredients.
Add eggs and then sifted dry ingredients. Then add molasses and water to Crisco and sugar mixture.
Beat with a rotary beater to mix thoroughly and pour into well-greased oblong cake pans and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves with vanilla sauce.
Serve 16 to 18.

title: funnel cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine eggs and milk.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to liquids.
Test mixture to see if it flows through funnel.
If too thick, add milk.
If too thin, add flour.
In an 8-inch skillet, heat oil to 360°. Lower bottom opening of funnel and with finger release batter
in hot oil in a continuous spiral.
Fry to golden, about 3 minutes. Using a spatula or tongs, turn the cake carefully.
Cook 1 more minute.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar; press into a 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes; cool.

title: heavenly jam
directions: Peel, stone and chop or mash peaches.
Add sugar and let stand overnight.
The next morning, add grated rind of 1 orange and the pulp and juice of both oranges.
Put into heavy saucepan and cook 30 minutes.
Add the cherries and juice.
Cook 30 minutes more. Pour into hot jars and seal at once.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from bones and cut meat into bite size.
Mix chicken and cubed bread with rest of ingredients, except crumbs.
Place in greased baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cinnamon refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix flour and granulated sugar.
Cut in butter with a fork. Add egg yolk.
Mix.
Form into 2 rolls.
Beat egg white slightly. Brush it on the roll and then roll the roll in a mixture of brown sugar and cinnamon.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut into slices about 1/8-inch in thickness.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until very lightly browned (golden in color).
Makes 40 to 60 cookies.
Bake on rack higher than the middle of the oven.

title: potato soup(slow cooker)
directions: Cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or cook on High for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir in evaporated milk the last hour.

title: butterscotch torte
directions: Mix flour, oleo and nuts. Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese and 10x sugar. Fold in the Cool Whip; then spread over crust.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter into baking dish. Add remaining ingredients. Pour Eagle Brand milk over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Boil hamburger in water until done.
Add other ingredients and cook a little longer.

title: punch recipe
directions: Add sugar to water in pan.
Bring to boil to make syrup.
Add syrup to Kool-Aid (mixed).
Add pineapple juice.
Chill.
Add ginger ale before serving.
(This can also make an ice ring.)

title: turnip greens
directions: Cook neck bones until done (about 2 hours). Add turnip greens. Let come to a boil. Add salt and pepper sauce. Let simmer on low until greens are tender. Serve with cornbread.

title: oyster cracker snack mix
directions: Mix oil and crackers; add next 3 ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Add Ranch Style dressing mix; stir.
Store in covered container.

title: chicken or turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cut up chicken or turkey into bite-size pieces.
Boil noodles with celery and carrots.
Drain.
In large bowl mix noodles, broth, mushroom soup, pimentos, celery and carrots.
Add grated cheese, reserving enough to put on top.
Bake at 350° about an hour in 9 x 13 pan.

title: smacker doodle cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine then add the other ingredients.
Pour into a
9 x 12 pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon and brown sugar across the top.
Top with butter patties.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sheryl's pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 15 minutes.
Gradually add 1 cup sugar to eggs. Add pumpkin and juice to mixture.
Sift dry ingredients and
add to mixture.
Spread out on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Top with
chopped
walnuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn
out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Roll together and chill.

title: pickled okra
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the vinegar, water and salt. Over a medium-high heat, bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes. While boiling, wash the okra and remove the stems. Divide them among 10 pint jars.
Divide the dill, garlic and jalapenos among the 10 jars.
Pour the hot mixture over the okra until totally covered.
Seal. Store in a dark place for 3 weeks to allow to pickle.
Chill before serving.
Preparation time:
20 minutes. Pickling time:
3 weeks.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Melt 1 cup chocolate chips and margarine.
Mix in sugar, eggs, flour and vanilla.
Stir in other cup of chocolate chips, marshmallows and nuts.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix
sugar
into
vinegar until dissolved.
Add to salad dressing.
Pour over 2 pounds shredded green cabbage.
Toss and chill
before serving.
Must use Miracle Whip salad dressing or it simply isn't good.

title: pat's jam cake
directions: Mix the eggs, shortening, sugar, apple butter, buttermilk and jam.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Add coconut, nuts and floured raisins last.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in three 9-inch pans.

title: family favorite cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Set aside. Preheat oven to 350°.
Place in mixing bowl the oil, eggs, vanilla and lemon extracts.
Mix well. Gradually add sugar.
Blend well. Gradually add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.
Remove immediately and cool on a rack.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix well and pour in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350 for 30 minutes.
When cool frost with cream cheese icing.

title: pie crust
directions: Add ice water to egg yolk and vinegar to make 1/2 cup.
Mix flour and lard to a consistency of coarse meal.
Add yolk/water, a little at a time, until mixture clings together.
Chill dough for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat milk enough to dissolve Knox gelatine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: aunt rita's fudge squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs
one
at
a
time and beat. Sift flour, cocoa and salt
together and add to creamed mixture. Lastly, add nuts and vanilla.
Bake
in a greased 15 x 12-inch (jelly roll) pan at
for
minutes or until done.
Cut into squares while hot,
then
cool in pan.
May be baked in a greased 13 x
9-inch pan, adjusting time accordingly.

title: cherry cola mold
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayo until smooth.
Dissolve gelatins in boiling water.
Stir into cheese mixture.
Drain cherries and pineapple measuring 1 1/2 cups syrup, then add syrup and cola to gelatin.
Chill until very thick.
Fold in cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Cut Smokies sausage into pieces.
Put on toothpick with pineapple chunk.
Microwave on High for 45 seconds.

title: crepe
directions: Mix together, pour a thin layer on griddle.
Cook until lightly brown on 1 side, turn over and lightly brown on other side.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: cream cheese
directions: Blend in a blender until smooth.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: In the bottom of the punch bowl, assemble a layer of cubed cake pieces, a layer of pudding and top with Cool Whip. Next, a layer of cake cubes, pudding, drained crushed pineapple, top with a layer of cool whip Next, a layer of cubed cake pieces, vanilla pudding, fresh blueberries and top with cool whip. Next, a layer of cubed cake pieces, pudding, bananas, and top with cool whip. Next a layer of cubed cake pieces, pudding,
sliced strawberries, and top with cool whip. This is a fun cake because you can make the layers of fruit as thick as you like.
If fresh fruit isn't easy to get, you can use canned pie filling.

title: flowerpot dirt
directions: Cream first three ingredients in small bowl.
In separate bowl, mix pudding and milk together. Fold in Cool Whip after pudding is mixed.
Gently stir first three ingredients into pudding and Cool Whip mixture.
Chop Oreos in food processor.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice.

title: chocolate chips cake
directions: Beat at medium speed two minutes. Bake at 350° in greased and floured Bundt pan about 1 hour.
Let cool 25 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pumpkin tea bread
directions: Add measured amount of sugar to oil.
Mix well.
Add pumpkin and eggs.
In a separate bowl, mix spices and flour well.
Add to liquid mixture.
Pour into ungreased angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
(Optional:
Add 1 cup nuts and 2/3 cup raisins.)
I use six 1-pound foil pans and cook about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Peel and slice the potatoes.
In an aluminum pan, sprayed with Pam, arrange potatoes any way in pan.
Put in the onion soup mix. Stir the potatoes and soup mix.
Put your butter or oleo on top of mixture, about 6 to 8 tablespoons.
Cover with aluminum foil and cook on grill.
Cooking time, 1/2 hour to 40 minutes.

title: frankfurters and noodles
directions: Cook frankfurters and onion in the butter until lightly browned.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix all ingredients, except crumbs.
Put in buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs and bake in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine pie filling, water and sugar.
Cook until it boils. Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir, then let stand until cool.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Into greased baking dish, layer (in this order) potatoes, salt, pepper, flour and onions all the way to top.
Sprinkle top with flour.
Cover with pats of butter and milk.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: seafood enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large skillet, saute onions in 1 Tbsp. butter until transparent.
Remove the skillet from heat, and stir in crab meat and shrimp.
Mix in 1 cup shredded cheese. Place a large spoonful of the mixture into each tortilla.
Roll the tortillas up around the mixture, and arrange in a 9x13 inch baking dish.
In saucepan, combine half-and-half, sour cream, 1/4 cup butter, parsley and garlic salt.
Stir until the mixture is lukewarm and blended.
Pour this sauce over the enchiladas and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 1-2-3 casserole (creamettes)
directions: Cook Creamettes as directed on the package.
Drain and chill. Add mushroom soup and tuna.
Mix well.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve hot. Luncheon meat, wieners, ham or chicken may be substituted for tuna.

title: waffles
directions: Mix together, leaving only small lumps.
Bake as directed on waffle iron.

title: square buckeye
directions: Mix the first 4 items and spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt the chocolate chips and the remaining stick of margarine and spread over evenly.
Cool; let set and cut into 1/2-inch squares. Nuts can be added.
Also, you can use crunchy peanut butter instead of smooth, if so desired.

title: cranberry and orange bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add cereal and raisins and stir.
Mix egg, oil, orange juice and cranberry sauce in separate bowl.
Stir into flour mixture, mixing until dry ingredients are moist.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with soft cream cheese mixed with orange marmalade.

title: caramels
directions: Mix sugar, butter and Karo; heat.
Add 1 can of milk and stir until it boils.
Add another can of milk so slowly that the mixture does not stop boiling.
Cook until it forms a soft ball in water.
Add vanilla.
Cool.
Cut in squares and wrap in waxed paper.

title: party rye pizza
directions: Cook sausage and ground turkey.
Drain, if necessary.
Cube Velveeta and add to cooked meat.
Stir until melted and spreadable. Spread on party rye slices.
Toast in oven for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: heath bars
directions: Pre-heat oven to 350°. Line large cookie sheet with aluminum foil and spray with PAM or cooking spray.
Lay graham cracker pieces on the sheet.
Boil butter and brown sugar for 6 minutes. Pour over the crackers making sure to cover all of them.
Bake for 6-8 minutes.
As soon as you take them from the oven, sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Allow to melt, then spread with a spoon or knife.
Put in refrigerator to cool and harden for about 3 -4 hours.
Break into pieces.
There is no need to refrigerate.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine dressings and cheese. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly and chill.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Put berries in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together in a separate bowl.
Sprinkle over berries. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in ovenproof dish.
Mix all other ingredients, except fruit and 1/2 cup sugar, and pour into dish. Mix together the fruit and 1/2 cup sugar and pour over mixture. Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in a kettle and sprinkle with 4 tablespoons salt; let stand overnight. Drain and add the remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil. Cook 1 minute.
Put in jars and seal.

title: light chocolate cake
directions: Put wet ingredients in bowl.
Add dry ingredients and milk. Beat.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2 inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, water and sugar until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and sherbet.
Pour 7-Up over sherbet.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Put coconut and nuts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make cake mix according to directions on package.
Pour over nuts and coconut. Melt margarine and mix with cream cheese; stir in powdered sugar. Spoon on dots on top of cake mixture.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cook at 350°.

title: dirt cups
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Gently stir in whipped topping and half of the crushed cookies. Place 1 tablespoon crushed cookies into bottom of 8 ounce paper on plastic cups.
Fill cups about 3/4 full with pudding mixture.
Top with remaining crushed cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
