If desired, decorate with gummy worms or gum drop flowers to resemble flowerpots.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: modern cobbler
directions: Place fruit, 1/2 cup sugar and water in a pan; bring to a boil. Mix together salt, 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk. Pour batter into a greased pan.
Pour fruit mixture on top of batter in pan.
Do not mix together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beets and greens
directions: Cut tops off beets, leaving 1-inch of the stems on to prevent beet from "bleeding" into the cooking water. Scrub beets. Cover with water in medium size pan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer until tender, about 45 minutes.

title: cornmeal rolls(makes 24 rolls)
directions: In saucepan, combine 1 3/4 cups water, cornmeal, sugar, oil and salt.
Cook over medium heat until mixture boils, about 10 minutes.
Cool at room temperature to 120° to 130°.
Place in mixing bowl.
Dissolve yeast in remaining water.
Add cornmeal mixture.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour to make soft dough. Turn onto floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl and turn once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Punch down.
Shape into 24 balls.
Place on greased baking sheets, brush with butter and sprinkle with cornmeal.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or golden brown.
Immediately remove from baking sheet.	Serve warm.

title: old time chess pie
directions: Mix flour and meal with sugar.
Beat eggs and yolks with mixture until light.
Add soft butter and mix all with milk.
Cook about 1 hour or until done in unbaked pastry shell.

title: baked cream cheese appetizer
directions: Unroll dough on lightly floured surface; press seams together to form 12 x 4-inch rectangle.
Sprinkle top of cream cheese with dill.
Place cream cheese, dill side down, in the center of dough. Enclose cream cheese in dough by bringing sides of dough together.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet; brush with egg yolk.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until brown.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: lobster or crab meat salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Prepare green beans.
Remove from heat.
Drain and set aside. Combine 1 tablespoon of margarine with the Special K and paprika. Set aside for topping.

title: mama's garlic fried chicken
directions: Wipe chicken with damp cloth.
Place in large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients, except flour; pour over chicken, covering all pieces well.
Cover bowl tightly, refrigerate overnight. Drain, dredge with flour.
Fry until done.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pork vegetable stir-fry(for 1)
directions: In 8-inch skillet with lid, place vegetable oil and meat. Cook on medium heat until brown (do not overcook).
When meat is ready, turn heat to high and add vegetables and garlic.
Stir to mix, then cover and let steam.
Check and stir occasionally.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a buttered glass casserole dish at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: many bean stew(vegetarian)
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in oil along with the paprika.
Add pintos, water and bay leaf; bring to a boil.
Simmer, about an hour.
Add kidneys and lima beans; simmer about another hour, then add remaining ingredients.
Check and stir occasionally, especially toward the end, to make sure there is enough liquid to prevent burning.
Simmer gently for another hour.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Thaw bag of hash browns. Mix all ingredients in bowl or in 9 x 13 sprayed pan. Bake for 1 hour. Top should be slightly golden.

title: hearty beef with wine(microwave)
directions: In large casserole, cook beef, bouillon and 1 cup water, covered, on High power 10 minutes, stirring once.
Add carrots, potatoes and onions; cook, covered, on Medium (50% power) 40 minutes, stirring twice.
Stir wine, flour and pepper together. Stir wine mixture, mushrooms and frozen peas into beef mixture. Cook, covered, on High 4 to 5 minutes, until tender.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix in order given and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes in a long greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
When done, spread a jar of marshmallow cream over cake.
Let cool and then ice.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Roll into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press out with fork dipped in cold water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool 1 minute; remove from pan.
Do not overbake.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Layer the chicken and broccoli in a casserole dish.
Mix mayonnaise and lemon juice together.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with grated cheese and then the bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chuck wagon chili
directions: Brown meat with garlic in large saucepan; drain.
Stir remaining ingredients except green onions.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add green onion; simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Ladle chili into bowls. Serve with toppings and additional picante sauce.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix.
Grease Bundt or angel food pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: whole wheat banana bread
directions: Measure flour, wheat germ, baking soda and salt into large bowl.
In bowl, combine the eggs, banana, honey, vegetable oil, lemon juice and vanilla until well blended.
Pour over flour mixture.
Add walnuts; stir with rubber spatula just until blended.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° until sides pull away from pan and pick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool on rack before removing.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce (enough to cover a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish). Chop onion; may be omitted or use as much as you like.
Layer on top of lettuce.
Chop cauliflower, put on top of onion.
Drain can of peas.
Spread on cauliflower.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar. Spread on peas.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cook bacon or use bacon bits and spread on top.
Cover and refrigerate before serving.

title: date nut bread
directions: Sift together the flour and salt.
Add boiling water and soda to dates.
Let stand.
Cream the sugar, egg and butter.
Add date mixture to this and blend well.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well. Add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased and lined loaf pans (2).
Fill each half full.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Cook the salt pork slowly in a small skillet until fat melts and the scraps are brown. Remove the melted fat to large heavy kettle. Stir fry onion in the fat five to eight minutes until pale golden.
Add remaining vegetables, water, salt and pepper.	Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat, add clams and clam liquid.
Cover and let stand 1/2 hour to blend flavors.
Return to heat and simmer about five minutes. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: mexican crepes
directions: Fry meat with onions and garlic; drain.
Place equal amounts in each tortilla along with cheese; roll up.
Mix soup, sour cream and chilies to make a sauce; pour over tortillas.
Bake, covered, until hot at 350°.

title: omelet in a bag
directions: Place eggs in zip lock bag.
Squish eggs in the bag.
Add any other ingredients you would like.
Close bag.
Mix well.
Place sealed bag in a pot of boiling water.
Your omelet should be ready in 5-10 minutes.
Open and eat from bag.

title: fried rice
directions: Chop and fry bacon.
Chop yellow onions and saute with bacon and bacon grease.
Cook pork with bacon and onions.
When pork is done, push meat and onions to side of pan.
Add eggs and scramble. Mix all with seasoning and a little soy sauce.
Add rice.
Add enough oyster sauce to flavor and color (about 1 1/2 tablespoons). After rice is done, top off with chopped green onions.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, celery, raisins and peanuts.
Combine mayo, sugar and curry powder for dressing.
Add crumbled bacon just before serving.
Add dressing; toss and serve.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 2 quart saucepan melt butter.
On a piece of wax paper combine bread crumbs, cheese, basil and garlic salt.
Dip chicken breasts in melted butter, then roll in bread crumbs to coat.
Place skin side up in ungreased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake in oven at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
While chicken is baking, add apple juice, onion and parsley to remaining melted butter.
When chicken is golden brown, pour butter sauce over and around.
Return to oven for 3 to 5 minutes more or just until sauce is hot.
Serve with sauce spooned over.
Good with wild rice as an accompaniment.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour filling into crust and chill for 2 hours.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook to boiling point, then simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn oysters
directions: In a colander, rinse frozen corn just until ice crystals disappear.
Place corn in a bowl.
Add milk, flour, egg, salt and pepper.
Stir to mix.
Cover with paper towel and set aside.
In skillet over medium heat, warm butter and oil.
After butter melts completely, carefully put 6 rounded spoonfuls of corn mixture into skillet.
Cook corn oysters for 2 or 3 minutes or until bottoms are golden brown.
Turn them gently and cook 2 or 3 minutes more or until both sides are golden brown.

title: dad's vinegar pie
directions: In top of double boiler, combine sugar, eggs, vinegar, cornstarch and water.
Cook over hot water until mixture is thick and smooth.
Stir occasionally.
Just before removing from heat, stir in the butter and lemon extract.
Pour into baked pie shell. Cool and serve with whipped cream, or may serve plain.

title: southwestern squash casserole(calabacitas)
directions: Saute the zucchini, onion, and garlic in the oil until just soft.
Mix together all ingredients and put in an oiled casserole dish.
Bake in a pre-heated 375 degree oven.
Cook for 20-25 minutes or until top begins to brown.
Serves 4-6.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Peel melon.
Cover with water and add 2 tablespoons lime.
Let stand overnight.
Next day drain and let stand 1 hour in clear, cold water.
Drain and cover with fresh water.
Cook 1 1/2 hours. Drain and cover with water with 1 small box ginger root.
Cook 2 hours and drain.
Make syrup of sugar, vinegar, cloves, spice and cinnamon in cheesecloth.
Pour over rind and cook until clear, about 1 hour.

title: zucchini meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and mix well.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Brown meat in margarine.
Sprinkle with half the sauce mix. Spoon cottage cheese over meat.
Top with layer of uncooked noodles and sprinkle with remaining sauce mix, basil, parsley and salt.
Pour juice over mixture making sure all is moistened. Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 35 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: spicy baked shrimp
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add shrimp; toss to coat.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake until shrimp are cooked through, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
Garnish with lemon wedges.

title: microwave pizza chicken
directions: Place coating mix, oregano and pepper into shaker bag.
Shake to blend.
Add chicken to bag and coat well.
Place in baking dish.
Cover.
Microwave on Full power for 6 minutes per pound of chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and microwave on Cookmatic level 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream. Set aside. Mix all other ingredients, then add soup and sour cream mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Mix scallops, bread crumbs, salt, lemon juice, butter, white wine and garlic powder together.
Lay raw shrimp on buttered baking dish, then scoop the bread crumb mix on top of each shrimp. Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Add to drained beef and heat to boiling the refried beans, tomato sauce, taco seasoning mix, chopped onion, chopped pepper, dry mustard and chili powder.
Pour into a large casserole dish. Spread with sour cream.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with Tostitos.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Scrub potatoes but do not peel.
Cook until just tender in boiling water.
(Optional:
Add a teaspoon of salt to each quart of water.)
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon on absorbent paper. Crumble.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: potato custard pie
directions: Boil
potatoes until done and drain.
Add margarine and mix well.
Add sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and eggs and beat well. Add milk
and
salt.
Mix
well.
Pour into a 9-inch crust and bake at 325°
until
crust
is
brown.
Set out and let cool. Very good.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt; set aside.
Next, cream butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla together. Gradually add the dry mixture to the butter mixture and when blended, add oats.
Form cookies the size of walnuts and roll in powdered sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten out. Bake at 350° until just light brown.
These are real soft and chewy.

title: crabmeat souffle
directions: Cube 4 slices of bread and spread in 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Mix together and spread on bread cubes the crabmeat, mayonnaise, onion, salt and celery.
Cube remaining bread and put on this layer.
Combine milk and eggs.
Pour over layer of bread cubes. Refrigerate overnight.
Let stand 2 hours.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven.
Combine soup and cheese and pour on top of casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Return to oven and bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and onion into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish. Add margarine,	pepper	and
Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and microwave on High for 15 to 20 minutes (microwave temperatures may vary).
Delicious and low calorie.

title: currant bread
directions: All ingredients are to be added one at a time and blended well.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Mix a cup of hot water with a package of Jell-O.
Add juice and rind; let cool but not set.
Beat milk until stiff (will not peak like egg whites but will be light and fluffy).
Add sugar or Equal.
Add Jell-O mixture and beat stiff again.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle top with graham cracker crumbs and chill.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Add 1 cup water to Lipton dry soup mix in container.
Cook until all is dissolved.
Add mixed vegetables as desired.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Add potatoes.
Add Season-All, bouillon, tomato soup and green pea soup.
Continue to simmer.
Add shrimp.
Simmer another 45 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms.
Trim ends.
Remove stems.
Finely dice stems and onions.
Saute in margarine to brown.
Add 1/4 cup bread crumbs and cheese.
Fill caps with mixture and bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken divine
directions: Boil and debone chicken (boil with bay leaf and basil).
Cook broccoli according to package directions until separated.
Drain and place broccoli in casserole.
Top with chicken.
Combine soup, water or broth, salad dressing and curry powder.
Pour sauce over casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with almonds.
This goes good with rice and a tossed salad.
Serves 2 to 3.

title: mother's creamed corn pudding
directions: Beat until all ingredients are thoroughly mixed. Pour into baking dish and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburg.
Add garlic, other seasonings, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer until thick.
Combine cottage cheese, salt, eggs, parsley, pepper and Parmesan cheese.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add flour mixture to zucchini mixture.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes in two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans (greased).

title: hamburger hash
directions: Cook rice.
In saucepan, prepare ground veal.
Cook and drain. Add tomatoes, green pepper, onion, chili mix, salt to taste and mushrooms.
Let cook in saucepan.
Pour mixture over rice and serve.

title: flounder in crumbs
directions: Place flounder in baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread diet mayonnaise on top of the fish.
Sprinkle with cornflake crumbs.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for about 10 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: corned beef loaf
directions: Separate corned beef and mix with other ingredients.
Put in a greased pan and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 9 to 10.

title: supreme beef casserole
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Return to skillet and add tomatoes, sauce, salt, sugar and garlic.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain.
Return to pan and blend in sour cream, cream cheese and green onions.

title: cranberries in the snow
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water to soften.
Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Cool.
Combine cottage cheese, sweetened condensed milk and coconut.
Stir in gelatin.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, water and milk well.
Refrigerate 5 minutes. Slice bananas (squeeze fresh lemon juice over bananas).
Whip cream; fold into pudding mixture.
Alternate layers beginning with pudding mixture, wafers and bananas ending with pudding mixture. Chill.
Makes a pretty trifle bowl dessert.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Cut up artichokes into 4 large chunks.
Mix mayonnaise, Romano cheese, garlic powder, pepper and hot sauce.
Stir in artichokes. Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour covered or 400° for 25 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered.
Serve hot with Triscuits.

title: acadian sauce(american)
directions: Chop tomatoes.
Set aside.
Reserve liquid from can.
Saute all remaining vegetables in butter until tender.
Add herbs and spices.
Cook 1 more minute.
Add tomatoes and reserved liquid from can.
Cook about 10 minutes more.
Discard bay leaf before serving.
Serves 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Can add green grapes, cut in half if you like.

title: country style steak
directions: Combine salt, pepper and flour.
Roll steaks in seasoned flour.
Brown steaks in the margarine in a heavy skillet or frying pan.
Mix together soup and water.
Pour mixture over steaks and let it come to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat to low and simmer until steak is tender.
As the steak cooks, more water may need to be added.
When the steak is tender enough, I cut the steak into bite size pieces before serving.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and salad dressing mix in medium size bowl until well blended. Stir in remaining ingredients and cover. Refrigerate until chilled, and serve with assorted cut-up vegetables.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: In pan, melt margarine and cheese.
Sift together sugar and cocoa.
Add cheese mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Makes 2 (9 x 12-inch) pans.

title: "chestnuts"
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, peanut butter.
Add Krispies.
Make into balls the size of chestnuts.
Chill.
With a toothpick dip the balls in the melted chocolate leaving a hole on top to look like a chestnut.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add potatoes; stir well.
Sprinkle milk over flour mixture.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Prepare as regular biscuits; cook at 450° for about 10 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and egg.
Add cream and vanilla.
Sift together remaining ingredients well and add.
Mix well.
Chill dough.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Put rum, honey and peel in a mug.
Add boiling water.
Stir. Top with butter.
Yields 1 drink.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla with the zucchini and pineapple.
Fold in the sifted, dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes two large or three small loaves.

title: grilled pork chops
directions: Melt oleo; add other ingredients and mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Keep warm while basting.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Fry ground beef; drain. In a casserole dish, mix frozen Tater Tots, soup, onion, garlic and black pepper. Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes. Sprinkle grated cheese on top before baking.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Put all ingredients (except oil) in the blender.
Add the oil gradually.
Beat until thick.
Do not refrigerate.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain grease; set aside.
Take a glass casserole dish and grease it.
Line the dish with the crescent rolls.
Pour sausage on top of that.
Sprinkle cheese on top of the sausage.
In a bowl, mix the eggs and milk.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and add sugar.
Mix well.
Let set 2 to 8 hours.
Fold in fruits, marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip or whipped cream.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Add sugar to margarine. Mix in pudding mix, eggs and vanilla. Combine flour and soda. Gradually add to batter. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in a casserole dish.
Add mushroom soup. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbling.

title: marlene's chicken oriental
directions: Cook chicken in butter until white.
Add pineapple juice, cream of chicken soup, vinegar, honey and garlic; cook for 20 minutes. Add green pepper; cook for 5 minutes.
Add pineapple chunks.
Heat and serve over rice.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Wash and dry fresh cucumbers.
Cover with brine (1 cup salt dissolved in 1 gallon cold water).
Let stand 24 hours.
Drain. Puncture each cucumber in 2 or 3 places with needle.
Simmer (do not boil) 1/2 of the sugar, the spices, vinegar and water for 30 minutes.
Add cucumbers and simmer 15 minutes.
Let stand 2 days. Drain off the liquid.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Be sure this is mixed very well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar plum pudding
directions: Mix together.
Put in rectangular pan and bake in 325° oven until set.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Combine macaroni, egg and next 5 ingredients; stir well.
Spoon mixture into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs and butter, stirring well. Sprinkle over macaroni.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, 1 cup of margarine and cocoa.
Beat eggs with vanilla.
Add flour.
Beat well.
Add coconut, coconut extract and chopped nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan (well-greased).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Immediately after taking from the oven, spread with marshmallow cream.
Spread with Mississippi Mud Cake Frosting.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cut blocks of frozen green beans in quarters.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Add mushrooms.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over beans.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bread muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix sugar, egg whites, water, applesauce and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into muffin pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° until done. Makes 24 muffins.
Contains 197 calories and .3 fat grams.

title: caesar salad
directions: Place garlic cloves through garlic press and put into olive oil in wooden bowl.
Add anchovies and press all of these with fork.
Add vinegar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and pepper and egg yolk.
Mix well.
Add lettuce leaves and mix well.
Add croutons and Parmesan cheese and mix well.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine and mix first 6 ingredients.
Beat well.
Add vanilla. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top, then swirl into batter with a fork. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool, then sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: fruited-sausage stuffing
directions: in a skillet, brown pork sausage, stirring to break into bits. Add celery and onion.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently. Combine with remaining ingredients.
Use to stuff 12 to 14 pound turkey.

title: creamy chocolate filling
directions: Combine confectioners sugar and egg.
Combine sugar and water. Boil for 1 minute.
Add slowly to first mixture; blend well.
Add Crisco, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Spreads easily.
Does not dry out.

title: creole meat loaf
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in ketchup.
Combine 1/2 cup of this mixture with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg and salt.
Form into loaf (8 x 4 x 1/2-inch) in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Serve remaining sauce cold or heated over meat loaf. Makes 6 servings.

title: mandarin cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Divide cake batter between 4 floured and greased cake pans. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: lime mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Add cold water and lemon juice. Add softened cream cheese; mix until well blended. Chill until almost firm. Fold in marshmallows, pineapple, coconut and nuts (about 2 hours). Mix again. Pour into mold. Chill until firm.

title: grandmother's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix butter and Crisco until it becomes creamy.
While beating gradually, add sugar.
Alternate a small amount of flour, then an egg until all in bowl, beating continually.
Add vanilla and stir.
Bake in greased Bundt pan 1 hour.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Brown onion and green pepper.
Add hamburger meat and brown. Drain off most of grease.
Add pork and beans, corn and spaghetti sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with cornbread and salad.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: In medium bowl mix 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, butter and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In a small bowl mix remaining dry ingredients.
Sprinkle atop batter.
Pour hot water on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: fritters "bread"(friganice)
directions: Combine yeast, warm milk and 1/2 cup flour and set aside to rise.
Beat egg yolks; add yeast mixture and remaining ingredients; beat well.
Cover and let rise until double.
Preheat about 2 1/2 cups of oil in a skillet.
Drop the batter in oil with a tablespoon.
Brown on each side.
Remove from skillet and allow to drain.
Sprinkle with sugar, if desired, or serve with sour cream.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, egg yolks, flour, vanilla and sour cream. Cook to desired consistency; add 1 tablespoon hot water, if needed.
Add raisins and nuts to mixture.
Pour into pie crust. Beat egg whites for meringue; spoon on filling.
Bake until brown.

title: traditional sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Combine eggs, sweet potato, sugar and spices in mixer.
Pour into crust and bake for 45 minutes or until knife inserted into the middle comes out clean.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil 2 1/2 cups water and sugar together to make a thin syrup. Let cool.

title: grandmother's beef surprise
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown beef and onion together; pour off excess fat.
Pour in tomatoes, water and corn.
When this comes to a boil, put in macaroni.
Simmer until macaroni is tender, then add tomato paste and Ranch Style beans.
Stir.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Turn heat off.
Let sit 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with hot cornbread and tea.

title: venison marinade
directions: Add together as listed.
Stir well.
Pour over venison. Marinate 24 hours in refrigerator.
Cook meat as you desire, until tender.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage with onion and bell pepper.
Fix macaroni completely.
Mix together in large bowl; add sour cream and tomatoes.
Pour a little juice from tomatoes.
Mix up.
Pour a layer of casserole in dish.
Grate cheese.
Continue layering until all gone.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: In a blender, add cold milk, then sprinkle in gelatine.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Pour in hot milk; blend at low speed until gelatine is well dissolved (about 2 minutes).
Add peanut butter and sugar to mixture; blend at low setting.
Pour mixture into crust, then sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Chill for 3 hours. For easy cutting, slice with a hot, wet knife.

title: cherry chocolate rum squares
directions: Mix all together.
Grease and flour 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread evenly and bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: In saucepan, combine water, vinegar, oil, garlic, pepper and salt.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and chopped herbs; set aside to cool, stirring occasionally.
Spoon cooled mushrooms into jar, packing snugly. Pour liquid over mushrooms to cover.
Tuck a sprig or two of fresh herb into jar.
Cover; refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Bring to room temperature before serving.
Makes 2 (8 ounce) jars.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix.
Mix soup, milk, chicken, peas and thyme.
Spoon stuffing mix over ingredients.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ketchup, vinegar, water, margarine, chili powder, brown sugar and squeeze juice from lemon. Cook over low heat until thick. I put a few slices of lemon in sauce while cooking. If sauce is too thin, add ketchup. If sauce is too thick, add a little water.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix meat, salt, pepper, rice, 1/2 tomato paste, 1/4 cup water or more until quite soft.
(Don't forget the rice absorbs moisture.)
Roll mixture in cabbage leaves and put into and cover with other ingredients.
Add enough tomato paste and water to cover.
Simmer 2 1/2 hours at least.

title: chocolate chocolate chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into Bundt pan sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: date rocks
directions: Mix dates and nuts well with 2 tablespoons of flour.
Cream shortening with brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add soda dissolved in hot water alternately with flour and salt, then add nuts and dates.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) until light brown, about 13 minutes.
Makes 70 cookies.

title: egg in potato nest
directions: Fry bacon in small skillet and set aside.
Pour off all except 1 tablespoon fat and add butter.
Shred raw potato; add onion salt and pepper.
Fry until potatoes are lightly brown, about 10 minutes.
Form a circle of potatoes.
Carefully drop egg in center and fry to desired doneness.
Serve with bacon.
Serves 1.

title: crunchy baked fish fillets
directions: Thaw frozen fish.
Combine melted butter or margarine, garlic and herbs.
Arrange fillets, skin side up, in a shallow 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking dish.
Brush with butter mixture and 1/2 of the crumbs.
Turn fillets and repeat process with remaining butter mixture and crumbs.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serves 6.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Combine sugar, flour and milk; add to the melted butter.
Place peaches in mixture and bake at 350° until brown.

title: peppermint candy canes(makes 24 servings)
directions: Line 2 large baking sheets with wax paper; set aside.
Fit a large pastry bag with a 1/4-inch round tip.
Dip a cotton swab in red food coloring; paint 5 or 6 lengthwise parallel lines inside bag; set aside and let stripes dry completely.

title: weezie's potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with 1/2 cup melted butter and (optional) 2 cups crushed corn flakes or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.
Makes 1 cup.

title: date or raisin sandwich cake
directions: Mix together like pie crust.

title: lime vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve jello with water and let cool slightly.
Then mix all remaining ingredients (except cream cheese) into shallow dish and let jell.
Before serving you may spread softened cream cheese on top, if desired.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix ingredients well and store in an airtight container. Making hot chocolate for 1 use:
1/3 cup mix, 3/4 cup hot water and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Making hot chocolate for 4 use:
1 1/3 cups mix, 3 3/4 cups hot water and 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: chocolate toffee candy cookies
directions: Note:
This is a wonderful cookie everyone will ask you for the recipe.
I guarantee it.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse and dry mushrooms.
Remove stems.
Set the caps aside and mince the stems.
Melt the butter in a large skillet and add the onions and mushroom stems.
Add the sausage and saute until the onions are soft and the sausage is browned.
Place in a large bowl and add the remaining ingredients except for mushroom caps; blend well.
Place the caps on a lightly greased baking pan and stuff with the sausage mixture.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
I prefer to cook mine in the microwave.
Cook according to the size of your microwave.
Add ketchup on top.

title: stuffed meat rolls(very good)
directions: Combine ground beef, milk, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pat mixture into 4-inch squares.
Cook celery and onion in butter or margarine until tender but not brown.
Add bread crumbs; mix well. Season.

title: dilly bread
directions: Soften yeast in water; set aside.
In mixing bowl, combine cottage cheese, sugar, onion, butter, dill seed, salt, soda, & egg. Mix until blended.
Stir in yeast.
Gradually add flour to form stiff dough.
Cover & let rise in warm place for 1 hour.
Stir down dough.
Turn into well greased 8-inch round casserole about 1 1/2 qt. size.
Let rise 40 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes. Brush with butter.
Cut into wedges to serve.

title: five-three
directions: Mash bananas. Add lemon juice, orange juice, sugar and water. Stir well. Let set in the refrigerator ice tray. Freeze.

title: grandma's meatball soup
directions: Roll ground chuck into small meatballs.
Put in a stock pot with 6 cups water; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 to 45 minutes; then add all other ingredients and cook over low heat until all vegetables are tender (approximately 30 minutes).
Serve over soup pasta (optional).

title: oyster casserole
directions: Place 3 dozen drained oysters in shallow Pyrex dish.
(A Pyrex pie plate will do.)
Sprinkle with parsley and green onions and sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Melt 1 stick of butter.
Add juice of 1 lemon, mustard and Worcestershire sauce and pour over the crumbs.
This may be served in ramekins.
Bake in 450° oven until oysters curl and crumbs are brown, about 10 to 15 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in thin slices.
Put 1/2 potatoes in a layer on bottom of greased oblong pan.
Sprinkle with a little flour, butter, salt and pepper.
Make layers until all ingredients are used.
Add warm milk until the potatoes are almost covered.
Bake at 400° for 90 minutes.
Remove cover for last 10 minutes.
If creamier potatoes are desired, leave cover on.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk and cook on stove top in saucepan over medium heat.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat and pour into plate and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in the oleo. Add flour, Worcestershire sauce, water and broth. Simmer for 1 hour or until onions are tender. Serve with toasted bread with butter, Parmesan cheese and garlic salt. Cut toast up into small pieces. Top soup and croutons with Mozzarella cheese.

title: caramels
directions: Use a heavy 3-quart saucepan and a long wooden spoon.
Melt butter.
Add sugar, milk and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a full boil and cook 12 to 15 minutes to firm ball stage.
Remove from heat and blend in vanilla.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut into squares when firm.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Mix all well.
Put layer of lasagna in pan, uncooked.
Add layer of chicken, layer of cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Repeat for 3 layers.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until tender (not mushy). Drain.
Cut onion into rings.
Cut pepper into rings (no seeds). Combine onion and pepper with cooked carrots in heat-proof bowl. Combine all other ingredients in a saucepan.
Slowly bring to simmer over medium heat.
Remove from heat and pour over carrots, onions and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold. (Will keep 2 to 3 weeks.)
Serves 8.

title: caramel icing
directions: Bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into 3 (9-inch) pans and bake in a 350° oven until done.
Put applesauce or apple butter between each layer.
